dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT to_char(to_timestamp (M::text, 'MM'), 'TMmon') as M,
       Country,
       SUM(ProfitEquity) 
  FROM
(SELECT
  date_part('year', to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) as Y
  ,date_part('month',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) as M
  ,users."Country" as Country
  ,daily."ProfitEquity" as ProfitEquity
  ,rank() OVER (PARTITION BY date_part('year',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")),date_part('month',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) ORDER BY to_timestamp(daily."Datetime") DESC) as is_day_in_month
FROM mt5_daily_2019 daily
JOIN mt5_users users ON daily."Login" = users."Login"
WHERE  users."Group" LIKE '%maltainves%') a
WHERE a.is_day_in_month =1
GROUP BY a.M, a.Country
ORDER BY 3
'}}
name: 2) Total net client equity - in EURO (€) equivalent - for the accounts reported at Q.1.

description: Figures should be for the last day of the month in question. The total should include all money held as cash as well as equity in open CFD positions. This should be based on 'marked-to-market' valuations i.e. what would be the client's cash position if all CFDs were liquidated on the last trading day of that month. If your records are in another currency, please convert to € using the relevant month end marked-to-market FX rates (see ECB FX Reference Rates).

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') AS Month, users."Country" As Country, 
       SUM(CASE WHEN "Symbol" LIKE 'EUR%' and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%'
           THEN (deals."ContractSize")*(1/deals."Price")*("Volume"/10000)
           WHEN "Symbol" LIKE 'GBP%' and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest_GBP%'
           THEN (deals."ContractSize")*(1/deals."Price")*("Volume"/10000) 
           WHEN "Symbol" IN ('CL_BRENT','WTI_OIL','DAX_30','BTCUSDmf','ETHUSDmf','LTCUSDmf','BCHUSDmf','XRPUSDmf','DSHUSDmf','EMCUSDmf','EOSUSDmf')
           THEN (deals."ContractSize")*(deals."Price")*("Volume"/10000)*deals."RateMargin"
           ELSE (deals."ContractSize")*("Volume"/10000)*deals."RateMargin" END) AS EXPOSURE
FROM mt5_deals_2019 AS deals
JOIN mt5_users AS users ON users."Login" = deals."Login"
WHERE "Entry" = 0 -- In Trades only
and "Action" IN (0,1)
and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%' -- Change this for the Group you want (in case of MF something like malta_invest)
Group by to_char(deals."Time",'Mon'), users."Country"

'}}
name: 6) Total volume of trades by clients, for CFDs of any underlying asset class (all CFDs) in EURO (€).

creator: {'email': 'tony@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Tony', 'last_login': '2019-09-23T14:26:16.566Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 42, 'last_name': 'Cini', 'date_joined': '2018-11-23T08:12:34.195Z', 'common_name': 'Tony Cini'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select  open_positions.country As Country, 
       SUM(CASE WHEN open_positions.symbol_open LIKE 'EUR%' and open_positions.group_open LIKE '%maltainvest%'
           THEN (open_positions.ContractSize_open)*(1/open_positions.price_open)*(open_positions.volume_open/10000)
           WHEN open_positions.symbol_open LIKE 'GBP%' and open_positions.group_open LIKE '%maltainvest_GBP%'
           THEN (open_positions.ContractSize_open)*(1/open_positions.price_open)*(open_positions.volume_open/10000) 
           WHEN open_positions.symbol_open IN ('CL_BRENT','WTI_OIL','DAX_30','BTCUSDmf','ETHUSDmf','LTCUSDmf','BCHUSDmf','XRPUSDmf','DSHUSDmf','EMCUSDmf','EOSUSDmf')
           THEN (open_positions.ContractSize_open)*(open_positions.price_open)*(open_positions.volume_open/10000)*open_positions.RateMargin_open
           ELSE (open_positions.ContractSize_open)*(open_positions.volume_open/10000)*open_positions.RateMargin_open END) AS EXPOSURE
FROM (
      Select date_part('year',deals."Time") as Year_Open, to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') month_open, deals."Time" AS Time_Open, deals."Login" AS login, users."Group" group_open, deals."Price" AS price_open,
      deals."ContractSize" AS ContractSize_open, users."Country" As Country, deals."Volume" AS volume_open, 
      deals."RateMargin" AS RateMargin_open, deals."Symbol" AS symbol_open, deals."PositionID" AS Poistion_ID_Open
      From mt5_deals_2018 deals
      JOIN mt5_users users ON deals."Login" = users."Login"
      where deals."Action" IN (0,1) 
      and deals."Entry" = 0
      and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%'
      and date(deals."Time") < {{Time}}
      UNION
      Select date_part('year',deals."Time") as Year_Open, to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') month_open, deals."Time" AS Time_Open, deals."Login" AS login, users."Group" group_open, deals."Price" AS price_open,
      deals."ContractSize" AS ContractSize_open, users."Country" As Country, deals."Volume" AS volume_open, 
      deals."RateMargin" AS RateMargin_open, deals."Symbol" AS symbol_open, deals."PositionID" AS Poistion_ID_Open
      From mt5_deals_2019 deals
      JOIN mt5_users users ON deals."Login" = users."Login"
      where deals."Action" IN (0,1) 
      and deals."Entry" = 0
      and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%'
      and date(deals."Time") < {{Time}}
    ) open_positions-- These are all the open positions of Maltainvest
LEFT JOIN ( Select date_part('year',deals."Time") as Year_Close, to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') month_close, deals."Time" AS Time_Close, deals."Login" AS login, users."Group" group_close, deals."Price" AS price_close,
        deals."ContractSize" AS ContractSize_close, deals."Volume" AS volume_close, 
        deals."RateMargin" AS RateMargin_close, users."Country" As Country, deals."Symbol" AS symbol_close, deals."PositionID" AS Poistion_ID_Close
        From mt5_deals_2018 deals
        JOIN mt5_users users ON deals."Login" = users."Login"
        where deals."Action" IN (0,1) 
        and deals."Entry" = 1
        and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%'
        and date(deals."Time") < {{Time}}
        UNION
        Select date_part('year',deals."Time") as Year_Close, to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') month_close, deals."Time" AS Time_Close, deals."Login" AS login, users."Group" group_close, deals."Price" AS price_close,
        deals."ContractSize" AS ContractSize_close, deals."Volume" AS volume_close, 
        deals."RateMargin" AS RateMargin_close, users."Country" As Country, deals."Symbol" AS symbol_close, deals."PositionID" AS Poistion_ID_Close
        From mt5_deals_2019 deals
        JOIN mt5_users users ON deals."Login" = users."Login"
        where deals."Action" IN (0,1) 
        and deals."Entry" = 1
        and date(deals."Time") < {{Time}}
        and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%') close_positions
    ON open_positions."poistion_id_open" = close_positions."poistion_id_close"
    Where close_positions.login IS NULL 
    Group by open_positions.country', 'template-tags': {'Time': {'id': '86bf8cfa-876d-881e-7011-fb85e535b9e6', 'name': 'Time', 'display-name': 'Open Positions Up to', 'type': 'date', 'required': True, 'default': '2019-01-31'}}}}

description:
"Total (leveraged) GROSS exposure of all open CFDs across all retail client accounts i.e. absolute sum of total consideration (notional values) of all open client positions for all asset classes.
For example, suppose a client is long EUR 1,000 (notional value) in a given equity, short EUR 2,500 in a major index and long USD 10,000 in an FX CFD (e.g. USDJPY). The calculation would first convert the USD exposure into EUR (suppose the result is EUR 8,500). The total gross exposure in this case would then be the absolute sum of the individual position exposures, i.e. EUR 12,000 (= 1,000 + 2,500 + 8,500)"
name: _17) Total GROSS exposure of all client accounts on the last trading day of the month, for CFDs of any underlying asset class (TOTAL) in EURO (€).

creator: {'email': 'tony@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Tony', 'last_login': '2019-09-23T14:26:16.566Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 42, 'last_name': 'Cini', 'date_joined': '2018-11-23T08:12:34.195Z', 'common_name': 'Tony Cini'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT Month, Country, SUM(Profitable_Clients) AS Total_Clients
  FROM (
  SELECT to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') AS Month, deals."Login" AS Login, users."Country" As Country, 
  (CASE WHEN (SUM(deals."Profit" + deals."Commission" + deals."Storage") > 0) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Profitable_Clients
  FROM mt5_deals_2018 AS deals
  JOIN mt5_users AS users ON users."Login" = deals."Login"
  WHERE "Action" IN (0,1)
  and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%' -- Change this for the Group you want (in case of MF something like malta_invest)
  GROUP BY to_char(deals."Time",'Mon'), Login, Country
  ) AS temp
  Group by Month, Country
'}}
description:
An active account is an account that made one trade over the period in question or had an open position with "marked-to-market" revaluation over the period.

A client account is profitable on this measure if the net equity in the account at the end of the month plus any sums withdrawn and minus any deposits during the month would have exceeded the net equity in the account at the beginning of the month had no spreads, fees or charges been incurred and had no bonuses been earned or otherwise awarded. 

Any zero-balance accounts should be excluded. Where possible aggregate client accounts when they are linked to a single retail client.
name: _19) Total number of active accounts that made a profit over the relevant period (including spreads, fees and charges incurred and excluding any bonus received)  (all CFDs).

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT Month, Country, SUM(Profitable_Clients*Profit_on_Client) AS Total_Clients
  FROM (
  SELECT to_char(deals."Time",'Mon') AS Month, deals."Login" AS Login, users."Country" As Country, 
  (CASE WHEN (SUM(deals."Profit" + deals."Commission" + deals."Storage") < 0) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Profitable_Clients, SUM(deals."Profit" + deals."Commission" + deals."Storage") AS Profit_on_Client
  FROM mt5_deals_2018 AS deals
  JOIN mt5_users AS users ON users."Login" = deals."Login"
  WHERE "Action" IN (0,1)
  and users."Group" LIKE '%maltainvest%' -- Change this for the Group you want (in case of MF something like malta_invest)
  GROUP BY to_char(deals."Time",'Mon'), Login, Country
  ) AS temp
  Group by Month, Country
'}}
description:
"As above, but taking into account all the spreads, fees and charges incurred. 

Please express losses as negative numbers."

description:
"An active account is an account that made one trade over the period in question or had an open position with ""marked-to-market"" revaluation over the period.

A client account is profitable on this measure if the net equity in the account at the end of the month plus any sums withdrawn and minus any deposits during the month would have exceeded the net equity in the account at the beginning of the month had no spreads, fees or charges been incurred and had no bonuses been earned or otherwise awarded. 

Only profitable active accounts that had at least one position in cryptocurrency CFDs open during the relevant period should be included."
name: _25) Total number of active accounts that made a profit over the relevant period (including spreads, fees and charges incurred and excluding any bonus received)  (Accounts that have at least one cryptocurrency CFDs).

description:
"An active account is an account that made one trade over the period in question or had an open position with ""marked-to-market"" revaluation over the period.

A client account is profitable on this measure if the net equity in the account at the end of the month plus any sums withdrawn and minus any deposits during the month would have exceeded the net equity in the account at the beginning of the month had no spreads, fees or charges been incurred and had no bonuses been earned or otherwise awarded. 

Only active accounts that had no position in cryptocurrency CFDs open during the relevant period should be included."
name: _31) Total number of active accounts that made a profit over the relevant period (including spreads, fees and charges incurred and excluding any bonus received)  (Accounts that have no cryptocurrency CFDs).

"For the year 2017 the ESMA measures were not in place. In 2018 this would result in a negative balance protection. 

For firms providing negative balance protection in August 2017, please include instances in which clients went in to negative equity before their negative balance was restored by your firm.                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   For August 2018, negative balance protection will be in force. However, market gapping can lead to the client initially being closed out at a price that creates negative equity, with the account then recredited back to zero equity to meet the new requirement of negative balance protection.    
                                                                                                                          
We are looking for the number of times an account did/would have gone into negative equity in each of the relevant periods (August 2017 and August 2018)."

          free_gift, payment_agent_transfer, currency_conversion_transfer
        }'::VARCHAR[] AS exclude_payment_gateways,

        -- The items in this list of payment_type values will be excluded. Add or remove items as desired.
        '{
          arbitrary_markup
        }'::VARCHAR[]AS exclude_payment_types
)










-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE
SELECT UPPER(ps.srvname), gp.*
FROM param
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers() AS ps

    ps.srvname,
    param.start_date,
    param.end_date,
    param.exclude_payment_gateways,
    param.exclude_payment_types
) AS gp
ORDER BY gp.payment_time;"}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Accounting > Daily turnover report for date range
WITH params as (
    SELECT
        -- CH, CR, JP, MX, MLT, MF or any other client broker_codes
        'MX'::VARCHAR as broker_code,
        
        -- Start date
        '2017-09-18'::TIMESTAMP AS start_date,
        
        -- End date
        '2017-09-19'::TIMESTAMP AS end_date
)

-- If you find the report is missing a particular currency that should be included,
-- point DBA to the following instruction:
-- As postgres inspect: select update_type_daily_turnover_for_date_range(true);
-- then: select update_type_daily_turnover_for_date_range(false);


SELECT
  d.txn_date,
  d.total_buy_usd,
  d.total_sell_usd,
	d.buy_minus_sell_USD,
	d.total_open_bet_PL_USD,
	d.total_outstanding_bet_usd,
	d.agg_cash_bal_usd,
	d.pl_on_day,
	(jsonb_populate_record(NULL::daily_turnover_for_date_range, d.dat)).*
	
FROM params
CROSS JOIN LATERAL betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN LATERAL dblink(ps.srvname, $$
    SELECT * FROM reporting.daily_turnover_for_date_range_on(
      $$ || quote_literal(params.broker_code) || $$,
      $$ || quote_literal(params.start_date)  || $$,
      $$ || quote_literal(params.end_date)    || $$)
    $$) d (
    txn_date DATE,
	  total_buy_usd  NUMERIC,
	  total_sell_usd NUMERIC,
	  buy_minus_sell_USD        NUMERIC,
	  total_open_bet_PL_USD     NUMERIC,
	  total_outstanding_bet_usd NUMERIC,
	  agg_cash_bal_usd NUMERIC,
	  pl_on_day        NUMERIC,
	  dat              JSONB,
	  the_sql          TEXT
	)

WHERE params.broker_code = ANY( ps.broker_codes)"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Accounting > ICO amounts to date
SELECT
    COALESCE(ttime::TEXT,'Totals') AS ttime,
    SUM(aud_buy) AS aud_buy, SUM(aud_sell) AS aud_sell,
    SUM(bch_buy) AS bch_buy, SUM(bch_sell) AS bch_sell,
    SUM(btc_buy) AS btc_buy, SUM(btc_sell) AS btc_sell,
    SUM(etc_buy) AS etc_buy, SUM(etc_sell) AS etc_sell,
    SUM(eth_buy) AS eth_buy, SUM(eth_sell) AS eth_sell,
    SUM(eur_buy) AS eur_buy, SUM(eur_sell) AS eur_sell,
    SUM(gbp_buy) AS gbp_buy, SUM(gbp_sell) AS gbp_sell,
    SUM(ltc_buy) AS ltc_buy, SUM(ltc_sell) AS ltc_sell,
    SUM(usd_buy) AS usd_buy, SUM(usd_sell) AS usd_sell
FROM CROSSTAB($OUT$SELECT * FROM dblink('cr',
    $$
    WITH cbets AS (
        SELECT tt.transaction_time::DATE AS ttime, tt.action_type, ta.currency_code, SUM(abs(tt.amount)) AS amount
        FROM bet.financial_market_bet fmb
        JOIN bet.coinauction_bet cb ON cb.financial_market_bet_id=fmb.id
        JOIN transaction.account ta ON ta.id=fmb.account_id
        JOIN betonmarkets.client bc ON bc.loginid=ta.client_loginid
        JOIN transaction.transaction tt ON tt.financial_market_bet_id=fmb.id
        WHERE bc.email != 'ashkan.nemati@gmail.com'
        AND bc.email NOT LIKE '%binary.com'
        AND bc.email NOT LIKE '%regentmarkets.com'
        GROUP BY 1,2,3
    ),
    dc AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT cbets.ttime, cc.currency_code, acts.action_type FROM cbets CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.currency_config AS cc CROSS JOIN (VALUES ('buy'),('sell')) AS acts (action_type)
        WHERE cc.currency_code <> 'JPY'
    )
    SELECT dc.ttime AS ttime, dc.currency_code||'_'||dc.action_type AS act_curr, COALESCE(cbets.amount, 0) AS amount
    FROM dc
    LEFT JOIN cbets ON cbets.ttime=dc.ttime AND dc.action_type=cbets.action_type AND dc.currency_code=cbets.currency_code
    ORDER BY 1,2
    $$
    ) AS d(ttime DATE, act_curr VARCHAR, amount NUMERIC)$OUT$
)AS (
    ttime DATE,
    aud_buy NUMERIC, aud_sell NUMERIC,
    bch_buy NUMERIC, bch_sell NUMERIC,
    btc_buy NUMERIC, btc_sell NUMERIC,
    etc_buy NUMERIC, etc_sell NUMERIC,
    eth_buy NUMERIC, eth_sell NUMERIC,
    eur_buy NUMERIC, eur_sell NUMERIC,
    gbp_buy NUMERIC, gbp_sell NUMERIC,
    ltc_buy NUMERIC, ltc_sell NUMERIC,
    usd_buy NUMERIC, usd_sell NUMERIC
)
GROUP BY ROLLUP ((ttime))"}}

  FROM bet.coinauction_bet cb

  JOIN betonmarkets.client bc ON bc.loginid=ta.client_loginid
  WHERE t.transaction_time >= $$|| quote_literal( params.rpt_start) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
  AND t.transaction_time < $$|| quote_literal( params.rpt_end) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1day'::INTERVAL
  AND bc.email != 'ashkan.nemati@gmail.com'
  AND bc.email NOT LIKE '%binary.com'
  AND bc.email NOT LIKE '%regentmarkets.com'
  ORDER BY t.id
  $$) d (transaction_time TEXT, currency VARCHAR, amount NUMERIC, "type" VARCHAR, client_loginid VARCHAR, transaction_id TEXT)'}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Accounting -> MLT Summary Duty
WITH params AS (SELECT
  NULL::DATE AS rpt_start,  -- left as NULL, this will default to the first of last month -or- delete this line, remove the leading hyphens from the next line and specify the desired date
  --'2017-04-30'::DATE AS rpt_start,
  NULL::DATE AS rpt_end     -- left as NULL, this will default to the last of last month -or- delete this line, remove the leading hyphens from the next line and specify the desired date
  --'2017-05-02'::DATE AS rpt_end
),






-- Do not touch any code below here

raw AS (
	SELECT mtd.* FROM params CROSS JOIN LATERAL monthly_trans_details('MLT', rpt_start, rpt_end) AS mtd
),

drange AS (
	SELECT (MIN(transaction_time)::DATE::TEXT ||' / '|| MAX(transaction_time)::DATE::TEXT) AS val FROM raw
),

grp_mlt AS (
	SELECT
		broker_code AS "Broker",
		currency_code,
		action_type AS "Type",
		CASE WHEN residence='ie' THEN 'Irish Duty'::TEXT WHEN residence='gb' THEN 'UK Duty' ELSE 'Other' END AS label,
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER(WHERE action_type = 'buy'), 0) AS "Buys",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER(WHERE action_type ='sell'), 0) AS "Sells",
		NULL::NUMERIC AS "Gaming Yield",
		COUNT(*) AS "Number of Records"
	FROM raw
	GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
	ORDER BY 1,2,4,3
),
-- subtotals on grp_mlt
grp_mlt_subttl AS (
	SELECT
		"Broker",
		currency_code,
		'Total'::TEXT AS "Type",
		NULL::TEXT AS label,
		SUM("Buys") AS "Buys",
		SUM("Sells") AS "Sells",
		SUM("Buys" - "Sells") AS "Gaming Yield",
		SUM("Number of Records") AS "Number of Records"
	FROM grp_mlt
	GROUP BY 1,2,3
),
-- the MLT report
mlt_final AS (
	SELECT
		"Broker",
		currency_code AS "Currency Code",
		"Type",
		label AS "UK Duty",
		"Buys",
		"Sells",
		("Buys" - "Sells") AS "Gaming Yield",
		"Number of Records"
	FROM (
		SELECT * FROM grp_mlt
		UNION ALL
		SELECT * FROM grp_mlt_subttl
	) AS t1
	ORDER BY 1, 2, 3, 4 NULLS LAST, 5
)

-- this is our final MLT report
SELECT (SELECT val FROM drange) AS "Report Dates", * FROM mlt_final
UNION ALL
SELECT
	(SELECT val FROM drange) AS "Report Dates",
	"Broker",
	'Total'::TEXT,
	NULL,
	NULL,
	SUM("Buys"),
	SUM("Sells"),
	SUM("Gaming Yield"),
	SUM("Number of Records")
FROM grp_mlt_subttl
GROUP BY 2'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Accounting -> MX Summary Duty (v2)
WITH params AS (SELECT
  NULL::DATE AS rpt_start,  -- left as NULL, this will default to the first of last month -or- delete this line, remove the leading hyphens from the next line and specify the desired date
  --'2017-04-30'::DATE AS rpt_start,
  NULL::DATE AS rpt_end     -- left as NULL, this will default to the last of last month -or- delete this line, remove the leading hyphens from the next line and specify the desired date
  --'2017-05-02'::DATE AS rpt_end
),






-- Do not touch any code below here

raw AS (
	SELECT mtd.* FROM params CROSS JOIN LATERAL monthly_trans_details('MX', rpt_start, rpt_end) AS mtd
),

drange AS (
	SELECT (MIN(transaction_time)::DATE::TEXT ||' / '|| MAX(transaction_time)::DATE::TEXT) AS val FROM raw
)

SELECT * FROM (
	-- UK (GB) Clients that trade on randoms
	SELECT
		(SELECT val FROM drange) AS "Report Dates",
		currency_code AS "Currency Code",
		'UK_Duty'::TEXT AS "UK duty",
		action_type AS "Type",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'buy'), 0) AS "Buys",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'sell'), 0) AS "Sells",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'buy'), 0) - COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'sell'), 0) AS "Gaming Yield"
	FROM raw
	WHERE residence = 'gb'
	AND   is_random = TRUE
	GROUP BY 2,3,4

	UNION ALL

	-- All (MX) clients that trade on non-randoms
	-- AND all non-GB clients trading on randoms
	SELECT
		(SELECT val FROM drange) AS "Report Dates",
		currency_code AS "Currency Code",
		'Other'::TEXT AS "UK duty",
		action_type AS "Type",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'buy'), 0) AS "Buys",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'sell'), 0) AS "Sells",
		COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'buy'), 0) - COALESCE(SUM(amount) FILTER (WHERE action_type = 'sell'), 0) AS "Gaming Yield"
	FROM raw
	WHERE is_random = FALSE
	OR   (is_random = TRUE AND residence != 'gb')
	GROUP BY 2,3,4
) AS tmp
ORDER BY 2,3,4
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Accounting > Outstanding Contracts
WITH params AS (SELECT
    -- any valid broker code, like: CH, CR, MX, MF, MLT, etc.
    'MX'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,
    -- the report day effectively means what was in effect at 12:00 AM
    '2017-10-01'::DATE AS report_day,
    -- zero or more currency codes like '{GBP}' or '{GBP,EUR}' or even '{}' for all currency codes
    '{}'::VARCHAR[] AS currency_code
)





-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN LATERAL dblink(ps.srvname, $OUT$

WITH openz AS (SELECT * FROM dblink('dc', $IN$

	SELECT eb.account_id, eb.effective_date, eb.balance, ep.financial_market_bet_id, ep.marked_to_market_value AS mtm_value
	FROM accounting.end_of_day_balances AS eb
	LEFT JOIN accounting.end_of_day_open_positions AS ep ON ep.end_of_day_balance_id = eb.id
	WHERE eb.effective_date = $IN$|| quote_literal( $OUT$ || quote_literal( params.report_day ) || $OUT$ ) ||$IN$::TIMESTAMP
	
	$IN$) AS d (account_id BIGINT, effective_date TIMESTAMP, balance NUMERIC, fmb_id BIGINT, mtm_value NUMERIC)
),
inr AS (
SELECT
	bc.loginid,
	ta.currency_code,
  openz.effective_date, 
	openz.balance AS account_balance,
	SUM(openz.mtm_value) AS total_open_bets_value,
	SUM(openz.mtm_value - fmb.buy_price) AS total_open_bets_profit,
	openz.balance + COALESCE(SUM(openz.mtm_value), 0) AS total_equity,
	-- there is no magic to the following format... it's just the legacy format Accounting is accustomed to
	string_agg('1L ' || fmb.buy_price || ' ' || fmb.short_code || ' (' || openz.mtm_value || ')', '+') AS portfolio
FROM openz
JOIN transaction.account AS ta ON ta.id = openz.account_id
JOIN betonmarkets.client AS bc ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
LEFT JOIN bet.financial_market_bet AS fmb ON fmb.id = openz.fmb_id
WHERE bc.broker_code = $OUT$ || quote_literal( params.broker_code ) || $OUT$
$OUT$ || CASE WHEN cardinality( params.currency_code ) > 0 THEN 'AND ta.currency_code = ANY(' || quote_literal( params.currency_code ) || '::VARCHAR[])' ELSE '' END || $OUT$
GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
)
SELECT
    loginid,
    currency_code,
    effective_date,
    account_balance,
    COALESCE(total_open_bets_value, 0) AS total_open_bets_value,
    COALESCE(total_open_bets_profit, 0) AS total_open_bets_profit,
    total_equity,
    portfolio

FROM inr
WHERE account_balance <> 0 OR total_open_bets_value IS NOT NULL OR total_open_bets_profit IS NOT NULL

$OUT$) AS dbl (
    loginid VARCHAR,
    currency_code VARCHAR,
    effective_date DATE,
    account_balance NUMERIC,
    total_open_bets_value NUMERIC,
    total_open_bets_profit NUMERIC,
    total_equity NUMERIC,
    portfolio TEXT
)
WHERE broker_code = ANY (ps.broker_codes)
    
"}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Accounting > Pay Agent report -v1
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2019-01-01'::DATE AS start_date,
  '2019-02-28'::DATE AS end_date
)

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$

SELECT
    TO_CHAR(pp.payment_time, 'Mon') AS "MONTH",
    pp.payment_time::DATE           AS "Date",
    pa.client_loginid               AS "Loginid",
    pa.payment_agent_name           AS "PA Name",
    pa.target_country               AS "PA Country",
    COALESCE(
        df.payment_processor,
        CASE WHEN ppg.description > '' THEN ppg.description ELSE pp.payment_gateway_code END
        )                           AS "Method",
    COALESCE(bw.bom_bank_info, df.payment_processor, ppc.currency_code, 'n/a')        AS "Bank/Wallet",
    pa.currency_code                AS "Original Currency",
    pp.amount                       AS "Original Currency Amount",
    transaction.round_amount('USD', pp.amount * exch.rate)  AS "USD Amount",
    pp.remark                       AS "Payment Remark"
FROM betonmarkets.payment_agent AS pa
JOIN transaction.account AS ta
    ON ta.client_loginid=pa.client_loginid
JOIN payment.payment AS pp
    ON pp.account_id=ta.id
JOIN payment.payment_gateway AS ppg
    ON ppg.code=pp.payment_gateway_code
LEFT JOIN payment.doughflow AS df
    ON df.payment_id=pp.id
LEFT JOIN payment.bank_wire AS bw
    ON bw.payment_id=pp.id
LEFT JOIN payment.cryptocurrency AS ppc
    ON ppc.payment_id=pp.id
LEFT JOIN data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(pa.currency_code, pp.payment_time) exch (rate)
    ON true
WHERE $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP <= pp.payment_time AND pp.payment_time < $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date +1) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
  AND pp.payment_gateway_code NOT IN ('free_gift', 'payment_agent_transfer', 'currency_conversion_transfer', 'affiliate_reward', 'account_transfer')
  AND pp.amount > 0

$$) dbl (
  "MONTH" TEXT,
  "Date" TEXT,
  "Loginid" TEXT,
  "PA Name" TEXT,
  "PA Country" TEXT,
  "Method" TEXT,
  "Bank/Wallet" TEXT,
  "Original Currency" TEXT,
  "Original Currency Amount" TEXT,
  "USD Amount" TEXT,
  "Payment Remark" TEXT
)
order by 2,3'}}

dataset_query:
{'native': {'query': "--Accounts depositing from 1 IP

select
ip,
sum(amount),
count (distinct client_loginid) as number,
string_agg (distinct cast ((client_loginid) as text), ';') as clients,
string_agg (distinct cast ((residence) as text), ';') as countries

from 
(SELECT
--d.payment_id,
d.ip_address as ip,
d.transaction_type,
t.amount,
d.created_by,
--t.account_id,
a.client_loginid,
c.residence,
t.transaction_time::timestamp::date as day,

case WHEN client_loginid IN (select client_loginid from betonmarkets.payment_agent) THEN 'Yes'
Else 'No'
end payment_agent_status
--count(d.payment_id) as number,
--string_agg (distinct cast ((client_loginid) as text), ';') as logins
FROM payment.doughflow d
join transaction.transaction t on d.payment_id = t.payment_id
join transaction.account a on a.id=t.account_id
join betonmarkets.client c on c.loginid=a.client_loginid 
where created_by = 'INTERNET'
and transaction_type = 'deposit'
and t.transaction_time >= Now()- '24 hour':: interval
order by client_loginid desc
) i
where payment_agent_status = 'No'
group by ip
order by number desc"}, 'type': 'native', 'database': 2}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with by_minute_data as
(
    select 
        to_timestamp(((extract(epoch from purchase_minute)::bigint)/(60*6))*360) as six_minute,
        market,
        sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
        sum(profit) as profit
    from
    (
        select 
            currency_code,
            purchase_minute,
            market,
            total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
            profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
        from
        (
            select
                ta.currency_code,
                bm.market, 
                date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
                sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
                sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
            from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
            on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
            left join transaction.account ta
            on ta.id= fmb.account_id
            where purchase_time >= current_date
            and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
            group by 1,2,3
        ) tmp
    ) tmp2
    group by 1,2
)

select
  market,
  six_minute,
  -- sum(amount) OVER (PARTITION BY circle_id ORDER BY ea_year, ea_month) AS cum_amt
  sum(profit) over (partition by market order by six_minute asc rows between unbounded preceding and current row)
from by_minute_data
order by 2,1"}}
description: since midnight GMT

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with by_minute_data as
(
    select
        date_trunc('hour', purchase_minute) as purchase_time,
        --to_timestamp(floor(extract(epoch from purchase_minute)::bigint/15)*15) as purchase_time,
        market,
        sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
        sum(profit) as profit
    from
    (
        select 
            currency_code,
            purchase_minute,
            market,
            total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
            profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
        from
        (
            select
                ta.currency_code,
                bm.symbol as market, --bm.market, 
                date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
                sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
                sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
            from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
            on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
            left join transaction.account ta
            on ta.id= fmb.account_id
            where purchase_time >= current_date
            and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
            group by 1,2,3
        ) tmp
    ) tmp2
    group by 1,2
)

    count(distinct binary_user_id) filter (where length(myaffiliates_token) = 32) as affiliated
from betonmarkets.client
group by 1'}}
name: Affiliated versus unaffiliated clients by residence

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
    --(call_buy - put_buy)/(call_buy + put_buy) as call_to_put,
    --(even_buy - odd_buy)/(odd_buy + even_buy) as odd_to_even,
    *
from
(    
    select
        underlying_symbol,
        start_time,
        expiry_time,
        sum(buy_usd) filter (where bet_type in ('CALL', 'CALLE')) as call_buy,
        sum(buy_usd) filter (where bet_type in ('PUT', 'PUTE')) as put_buy,
        sum(buy_usd) filter (where bet_type='DIGITODD') as odd_buy,
        sum(buy_usd) filter (where bet_type='DIGITEVEN') as even_buy,
        
        string_agg(client_loginid, ', ') as "clients",
        string_agg(myaffiliates_token, ', ') as "tokens",
        string_agg(staff_loginid, ', ') as "staff_ids"
        --string_agg("fmb_id", ', ') as "financial_market_bet_ids"
    from  
    (
    select
        fmb.id::text as "fmb_id",
        fmb.account_id,
        client_loginid,
        tt.staff_loginid,
        underlying_symbol,
        --bet_class,
        bet_type,
        --short_code,
        start_time,
        expiry_time,
        buy_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date::timestamp) as "buy_usd"
        --sell_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date::timestamp) as "sell_usd",
        --payout_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date::timestamp) as "payout_usd"
    from bet.financial_market_bet fmb 
	left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.id=fmb.account_id
	left join transaction.transaction tt
	on fmb.id=tt.financial_market_bet_id
    where purchase_time >= NOW()-'24 hour'::interval
    ) tmp left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on tmp.client_loginid=bc.loginid
    group by 1,2,3
) tmp2
where 
(abs((call_buy - put_buy)/(call_buy + put_buy)) < 0.2 and (call_buy+put_buy) > 100)
or
(abs((even_buy - odd_buy)/(even_buy + odd_buy)) < 0.2 and (even_buy+odd_buy) > 100)'}}
name: Affiliates fraud check

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with active_accounts as
(
select distinct account_id, binary_user_id from bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join transaction.account ta
on ta.id=fmb.account_id
where purchase_time >= date_trunc('week', current_date) + interval '-7d'
and purchase_time < date_trunc('week', current_date)
), all_clients as 
(
select binary_user_id, min(date_trunc('week', date_joined)) as week_joined from betonmarkets.client 
group by 1
)

select (extract(epoch from (date_trunc('week', current_date) - greatest(week_joined, date_trunc('week', '2018-06-01'::timestamp))))::bigint)/(24*60*60*7) as account_age, count (distinct aa.binary_user_id) from active_accounts aa left join all_clients ac
on aa.binary_user_id=ac.binary_user_id
group by 1
order by 1 desc

"}}
name: Age (in weeks) of currently active accounts

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'template-tags': {'Time': {'id': 'a85b87c9-8b1f-0cb9-9e72-16b9709ade1c', 'name': 'Time', 'display-name': 'Time', 'type': 'date'}}, 'query': 'Select  deals."Symbol",
       Count(Distinct(users."Login"))   AS Total_Clients,
             Count(Distinct(users."Login")) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)  AS Agent_Linked_Clients,
              

       SUM("Volume"/10000) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Volume,
       SUM(("Profit")*-1)  FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Profit,
       SUM(("Storage")*-1) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Storage,
       CASE WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 10 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 25 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 50 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 75 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(2.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 100 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.75/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 10 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 50 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 100 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       ELSE '0' END AS Agent_Commissions
   FROM mt5_deals_2019 AS deals
   JOIN mt5_users AS users ON users."Login" = deals."Login"
   and date("Time") = {{Time}}
   and "Symbol" IN ('Volatility 10 Index', 'Volatility 25 Index','Volatility 50 Index','Volatility 75 Index', 'Volatility 100 Index','HF Volatility 10 Index','HF Volatility 50 Index','HF Volatility 100 Index')
   and "Entry" IN (0,1,3)
   and "Action" IN (0,1)
 
   and users."Group" LIKE '%costarica%'
group by deals."Symbol"'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select date_daily, daily_pnl, Sum(daily_pnl_table."daily_pnl")  over (order by date(daily_pnl_table."date_daily")) as aggregated_PnL
From(
  Select date(to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) AS date_daily ,
  SUM (daily."DailyProfit" + daily."DailyStorage")*-1  + SUM(daily."Profit" + daily."ProfitStorage")*-1-LAG(SUM(daily."Profit" + daily."ProfitStorage")*-1,1) OVER (ORDER BY date(to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")))  as Daily_PnL
  From mt5_daily_2019 daily
  Where "Group" LIKE '%costarica%'
  group by date(to_timestamp(daily."Datetime"))
  order by date(to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) DESC) AS daily_pnl_table'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'with params as (select
       '2018-07-06'::TIMESTAMP AS start_date,
       '2018-07-07'::TIMESTAMP AS end_date
)
       
select output.*
from params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() as ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname,
$$
     select b.id, 
            b.purchase_time, 
            b.underlying_symbol, 
            b.payout_price, 
            b.buy_price, 
            b.sell_price, 
            b.start_time,
            b.expiry_time, 
            b.bet_type, 
            b.remark, 
            b.short_code, 
            b.sell_time, 
            a.client_loginid, 
            bm.market,

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- All contracts purchased in a date range, with source, affiliate ID, &c
with params as (select
       '2015-01-07'::TIMESTAMP AS start_date,
       '2015-01-21'::TIMESTAMP AS end_date
)
       
select output.*
from params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() as ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname,
$$
     select b.id, 
            b.purchase_time, 
            b.underlying_symbol, 
            b.payout_price, 
            b.buy_price, 
            b.sell_price, 
            b.start_time,
            b.expiry_time, 
            b.bet_type, 
            b.remark, 
            b.short_code, 
            b.sell_time, 
            a.client_loginid, 
            bm.market, 
            bm.submarket, 
            data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, b.purchase_time) as "exchange_rate",
            c.residence,
            b.tick_count,
            c.myaffiliates_token,
            t.source
     from only bet.financial_market_bet as b
     join transaction.transaction t on b.id=t.financial_market_bet_id and t.action_type='sell'
     join transaction.account a on a.id=b.account_id
     join betonmarkets.client c on c.loginid=a.client_loginid
     left join bet.market bm on b.underlying_symbol = bm.symbol
     --where market <> 'volidx' and
     where --market = 'forex' and
      --sell_time is not null and
     ((purchase_time between $$ || quote_literal(params.start_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP and $$ || quote_literal(params.end_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP) --or
           --(sell_time between $$ || quote_literal(params.start_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP and $$ || quote_literal(params.end_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP)
           )
      order by purchase_time
      limit 1000000 offset 0
$$) as output(id NUMERIC, 
        purchase_time TIMESTAMP, 
        underlying_symbol VARCHAR, 
        payout_price NUMERIC, 
        buy_price NUMERIC, 
        sell_price NUMERIC, 
        start_time TIMESTAMP, 
        expiry_time TIMESTAMP, 
        bet_type VARCHAR,
        remark VARCHAR, 
        short_code VARCHAR, 
        sell_time TIMESTAMP, 
        client_loginid VARCHAR,
        market VARCHAR,
        submarket VARCHAR,
        exchange_rate NUMERIC,
        residence VARCHAR,
        tick_count NUMERIC,
        myaffiliates_token VARCHAR,
        source VARCHAR)
--where output.market in ('forex')
--order by output.purchase_time
--limit 1000000 offset 0'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Change the Time to get trades for that duration (used for London 4 pm fix)
SELECT bs.*,
  data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(bs.currency_code, bs.purchase_time) as "ExchangeRate"
FROM (
select t.id, 
  a.client_loginid, 
  b.buy_price, 
  b.sell_price,
  b.start_time,
  b.purchase_time,
  b.sell_time,
  b.payout_price,
  b.expiry_time,
  a.currency_code, 
  c.residence,
  b.short_code,
  b.bet_type,
  b.underlying_symbol
from ONLY bet.financial_market_bet b /* fmb contains only closed trades */
join transaction.transaction t on b.id=t.financial_market_bet_id and t.action_type='buy'
join transaction.account a on a.id=b.account_id /* that last_modified has no value here because it will at least reflect the trade */
join betonmarkets.client c on c.loginid=a.client_loginid
where b.purchase_time > '2018-07-02T14:50:00'  /* USE A REASONABLE VALUE BEHIND YOUR start_time */
  and b.sell_time < '2018-07-02T15:10:00'
  and b.bet_type in ('CALLE','PUTE','CALL','PUT')
  and b.underlying_symbol like 'frx%'
  
  ---and b.short_code similar to '%T_S%'
) AS bs

WHERE bs.start_time > '2018-04-01' /* get rid of this if you don't really care about start_time */
  order by buy_price DESC'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
  a.client_loginid, 
  b.bet_type,
  b.buy_price, 
  b.sell_price,
  b.start_time,
  b.purchase_time, 
  b.sell_time, 
  b.payout_price, 
  b.short_code,
  c.residence,
  ((b.buy_price - b.sell_price)*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, b.purchase_time) ) as "CompanyProfit",
  w.*
from transaction.transaction t, 
  bet.financial_market_bet b, 
  transaction.account a,
  betonmarkets.client c,
  (SELECT 
    t.client_loginid, 
    SUM(t."CompanyProfit") AS "TotalCompanyProfit" ,
    SUM(ABS(t."CompanyProfit")) AS "TotalABSMoneyInOut",
    COUNT(t."CompanyProfit") AS "COUNTTrades",
    -SUM(t."CompanyProfit")/SUM(ABS(t."CompanyProfit")) AS "Profitability"
  FROM 
    (select a.client_loginid, 
      ((b.buy_price - b.sell_price)*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, b.purchase_time) ) as "CompanyProfit"
    from transaction.transaction t, 
      bet.financial_market_bet b, 
      transaction.account a,
      betonmarkets.client c
    where t.financial_market_bet_id = b.id
      and c.loginid=a.client_loginid
      and t.account_id = a.id  
      and t.action_type = 'buy'
      and short_code like '%_S0P_0') AS t
  GROUP BY t.client_loginid) as w
where t.financial_market_bet_id = b.id
  and c.loginid=a.client_loginid
  and t.account_id = a.id  
  and t.action_type = 'buy'
  and short_code like '%_S0P_0'
  and w.client_loginid = a.client_loginid
  and w."COUNTTrades">=100
  and w."Profitability">0.1
ORDER BY w."Profitability" DESC'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Audit > address change within interval
WITH params AS (SELECT
-- CH, CR, MF, MX, MLT, JP...
-- bear in mind that running against CR will produce a very large report that will probably take "forever" to run without a tight interval
	'MF'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,

	'2017-07-01'::DATE AS start_date,
	'2017-12-31'::DATE AS end_date
)




-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink (ps.srvname, $$
    WITH ref AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (loginid)
            loginid,
            address_line_1 AS add1,
            address_line_2 AS add2
        FROM audit.client
        WHERE stamp < $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
        ORDER BY loginid, stamp DESC
    ),
    
    diffs AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (ac.loginid, ac.address_line_1, ac.address_line_2)
            ac.loginid,
            ac.address_line_1 AS add1,
            ac.address_line_2 AS add2,
            ac.stamp
        FROM ref
        JOIN audit.client AS ac
             ON ac.loginid = ref.loginid
             AND (ref.add1 <> ac.address_line_1 OR ref.add2 <> ac.address_line_2)
        WHERE ac.stamp >= $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
        AND ac.stamp < $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
        ORDER BY ac.loginid, ac.address_line_1, ac.address_line_2
    )
    
    SELECT
        diffs.loginid,
        ref.add1 AS reference_address1,
        ref.add2 AS reference_address2,
        string_agg((diffs.stamp::DATE::TEXT ||': ('|| diffs.add1 ||', '|| diffs.add2 ||')'), ' # ' ORDER BY diffs.stamp) AS address_diffs
    FROM ref
    JOIN diffs
         ON ref.loginid = diffs.loginid
    GROUP BY diffs.loginid, ref.add1, ref.add2
$$) AS dbl(
    loginid TEXT,
    reference_address1 TEXT,
    reference_address2 TEXT,
    address_diffs TEXT
    )
WHERE params.broker_code = ANY(ps.broker_codes)
ORDER BY betonmarkets.loginid_sortable(dbl.loginid);'}}
description: Audit > address change within interval
name: Audit address change within interval

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Audit > first deposit -AND- address change within interval
-- these items are not considered deposits for the sake of this report
-- ('free_gift', 'compacted_statement', 'cancellation', 'closed_account', 'miscellaneous', 'affiliate_reward', 'payment_fee', 'virtual_credit', 'account_transfer', 'currency_conversion_transfer')
WITH params AS (SELECT
-- CH, CR, MF, MX, MLT, JP...
-- bear in mind that running against CR will produce a very large report that will probably take "forever" to run without a tight interval
	'MF'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,

	'2017-07-01'::DATE AS start_date,
	'2017-12-31'::DATE AS end_date
)

-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink (ps.srvname, $$
    WITH first_dep AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (pp.account_id)
            pp.account_id,
            pp.payment_time
        FROM payment.payment AS pp
        WHERE pp.payment_type_code NOT IN ('free_gift', 'compacted_statement', 'cancellation', 'closed_account', 'miscellaneous', 'affiliate_reward', 'payment_fee', 'virtual_credit', 'account_transfer', 'currency_conversion_transfer')
    -- no point in considering payment activity after the end date
        AND pp.payment_time < $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
        ORDER BY pp.account_id, payment_time
    ),
    
    ref AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (loginid)
            loginid,
            address_line_1 AS add1,
            address_line_2 AS add2
        FROM audit.client
        WHERE stamp < $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
        ORDER BY loginid, stamp DESC
    ),
    
    diffs AS (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (ac.loginid, ac.address_line_1, ac.address_line_2)
            ac.loginid,
            ac.address_line_1 AS add1,
            ac.address_line_2 AS add2,
            ac.stamp
        FROM first_dep
        JOIN transaction.account AS ta
             ON ta.id = first_dep.account_id
             AND first_dep.payment_time >= $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
        JOIN ref
             ON ref.loginid = ta.client_loginid
        JOIN audit.client AS ac
             ON ac.loginid = ref.loginid
             AND (ref.add1 <> ac.address_line_1 OR ref.add2 <> ac.address_line_2)
        WHERE ac.stamp >= $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
        AND ac.stamp < $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
        ORDER BY ac.loginid, ac.address_line_1, ac.address_line_2
    )
    
    SELECT
        diffs.loginid,
        ref.add1 AS reference_address1,
        ref.add2 AS reference_address2,
        string_agg((diffs.stamp::DATE::TEXT ||': ('|| diffs.add1 ||', '|| diffs.add2 ||')'), ' # ' ORDER BY diffs.stamp) AS address_diffs
    FROM ref
    JOIN diffs
         ON ref.loginid = diffs.loginid
    GROUP BY diffs.loginid, ref.add1, ref.add2
    
$$) AS dbl(
    loginid TEXT,
    reference_address1 TEXT,
    reference_address2 TEXT,
    address_diffs TEXT)
    
WHERE params.broker_code = ANY(ps.broker_codes)
ORDER BY betonmarkets.loginid_sortable(dbl.loginid);'}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Audit > First time deposits within interval
-- Which clients first deposited to their account within the specified interval
-- This actually reports the first "payment" record for a given client, regardless of what type of "payment" that is
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2017-06-01'::DATE AS start_date,
  '2017-07-15'::DATE AS end_date,
  '{MF}'::VARCHAR[]  AS broker_codes -- leave empty, {}, to lookup all broker_codes, otherwise one or more of CR,MF,MX,MLT,JP,CH
)






-- Do not change any code below here

SELECT d.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$
    SELECT
        ta.client_loginid,
        bc.broker_code,
        crnt.payment_time::TEXT AS payment_time,
        crnt.payment_gateway_code,
        crnt.payment_type_code
    
    FROM (
        SELECT DISTINCT ON (pp.account_id)
            pp.account_id,
            pp.payment_time AS payment_time,
            payment_gateway_code,
            payment_type_code
        FROM payment.payment pp
        WHERE pp.payment_time >= $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
          AND pp.payment_time <  $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
        ORDER BY pp.account_id, payment_time
    ) AS crnt
    
    JOIN LATERAL (
        SELECT MIN(payment_time) AS payment_time
        FROM payment.payment
        WHERE account_id = crnt.account_id
    ) realmin ON realmin.payment_time = crnt.payment_time
    
    JOIN transaction.account AS ta
         ON ta.id = crnt.account_id
    JOIN betonmarkets.client AS bc
         ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
    WHERE
        $$|| CASE WHEN CARDINALITY(params.broker_codes) > 0
                THEN 'bc.broker_code = ANY('|| quote_literal( params.broker_codes ) ||'::VARCHAR[])'
                ELSE 'TRUE'
             END
        ||$$
$$) AS d (
    client_loginid VARCHAR,
    broker_code VARCHAR,
    payment_time TEXT,
    payment_gateway_code VARCHAR,
    payment_type_code VARCHAR)
    
WHERE CARDINALITY(params.broker_codes) = 0 OR params.broker_codes && ps.broker_codes
ORDER BY 3;'}}

WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2016-01-01'::DATE AS p_start_date,
  '2018-12-31'::DATE AS p_end_date,
  'MF'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,                             -- except JP... leave empty, '', for all broker codes
  '{disabled, cashier_locked}'::VARCHAR[]  AS status_codes, -- values separated by commas like: disabled, cashier_locked, unwelcome
  TRUE::BOOLEAN AS zero_balances_only                       -- TRUE to only get balances != 0, otherwise FALSE gives all flagged accounts
)






-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT t.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$
SELECT 
    cs.client_loginid,
    c.broker_code,
    ta.balance,
    ta.currency_code,
    cs.status_code,
    cs.last_modified_date::TIMESTAMP(0) AS last_modified_date,
    cs.reason 
FROM 
    betonmarkets.client c
JOIN betonmarkets.client_status cs ON c.loginid=cs.client_loginid
JOIN transaction.account ta ON ta.client_loginid=cs.client_loginid
WHERE 
    ta.is_default
    AND cs.status_code = ANY( $$|| quote_nullable(params.status_codes) ||$$::VARCHAR[])
    AND cs.last_modified_date >= $$|| quote_literal(params.p_start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
    AND cs.last_modified_date <  $$|| quote_literal(params.p_end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
    $$|| CASE WHEN params.zero_balances_only THEN 'AND ta.balance <> 0'::TEXT ELSE '' END ||$$
ORDER BY cs.last_modified_date DESC
$$::TEXT) t (loginid VARCHAR, broker_code TEXT, balance NUMERIC, currency_code TEXT,status_code VARCHAR, last_modified_date TEXT, reason VARCHAR)
WHERE ps.srvname != 'jp'
AND (params.broker_code = '' OR params.broker_code = ANY (ps.broker_codes))"}}

WITH params AS (SELECT
    '2018-02-01'::DATE AS start_date,
    '2018-02-25'::DATE AS end_date,
  -- For client_loginids, use {} for all -OR- specify a list of one or more like this '{ClientID1}' , '{ClientID1,ClientID2}'
    '{CR48993}'::VARCHAR[] AS client_loginids
)





-- Do not change any code below here



SELECT
    t.agent_loginid,
    t.currency_code,
    SUM(t.amount) AS acct_differential,
    COUNT(t.agent_deposit) AS agent_deposit,
    SUM(t.amount) FILTER (WHERE t.agent_deposit) AS deposit_ttl,
    COUNT(t.agent_withdrawal) AS agent_withdrawal,
    SUM(t.amount) FILTER (WHERE t.agent_withdrawal) AS withdrawal_ttl,
    COUNT(t.xfr_in) AS xfr_in,
    SUM(t.amount) FILTER (WHERE t.xfr_in) AS xfr_in_ttl,
    COUNT(t.xfr_out) AS xfr_out,
    SUM(t.amount) FILTER (WHERE t.xfr_out) AS xfr_out_ttl

FROM params
CROSS JOIN LATERAL payagent_analysis(start_date, end_date, client_loginids) AS t
GROUP BY
    t.agent_loginid,
    t.currency_code
ORDER BY betonmarkets.loginid_sortable(t.agent_loginid), t.currency_code
"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT 
e."date",
round(avg(e.new_deposit_amount*e.exchangetousd_rate),2) as "Average_deposits_USD"
FROM
(
  SELECT 
  data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(d.currency_code, d."date"), d.* -- created exchangetousd_rate variable from currency_code
  FROM
  (
    SELECT 
    cast(f.transaction_time AS date) as "date", -- convert transaction_time to date format
    a.currency_code,  -- let currency_code as a
    coalesce(sum(f.amount) filter (where f.action_type='deposit'), 0) as new_deposit_amount
    FROM transaction.firsts f left join transaction.account a
    on f.account_id=a.id
    
    WHERE CAST(transaction_time AS date) BETWEEN CAST((NOW() - INTERVAL '1 day') AS date)
          AND CAST(NOW()  AS date)
    
    GROUP BY 1,2 
    ORDER BY CAST(transaction_time AS date) DESC

  ) d
) e

group by 1
order by 1 asc



'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
  to_char(d."day", 'D'),
  to_char(d."day", 'day') as "day_of_week",
  d."residence",
  round(avg(d."turnover_USD"),2) as "turnover_USD",
  round(avg(d."profit_USD"),2) as "profit_USD",
  round(avg(d.client_count),2) as "client_count"
from
(
select 
  "day",
  "residence",
  sum("turnover_USD") as "turnover_USD",
  sum("profit_USD") as "profit_USD",
  count(distinct client_loginid) as "client_count"
from
(
select
  da."day",
  ta.client_loginid,
  da.turnover*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, da."day") as "turnover_USD",
  da.loss*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, da."day") as "profit_USD"
from
  bet.daily_aggregates da left join transaction.account ta
on
  ta.id=da.account_id
) x left join betonmarkets.client bc on
x.client_loginid=bc.loginid
where "day" < now()::timestamp::date
and "day" >= (now() + interval '-31 day')::timestamp::date
--and residence in 
group by 1,2
order by 1 desc, 3 desc
) d right join 
(
select "day", "residence", sum("turnover_USD") as "turnover_USD", sum("profit_USD") as "profit_USD"
from
(
select
  da."day",
  ta.client_loginid,
  da.turnover*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, da."day") as "turnover_USD",
  da.loss*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, da."day") as "profit_USD"
from
  bet.daily_aggregates da left join transaction.account ta
on
  ta.id=da.account_id
) x left join betonmarkets.client bc on
x.client_loginid=bc.loginid
where "day" < now()::timestamp::date
and "day" >= (now() + interval '-1 day')::timestamp::date
--and residence in 
group by 1,2
order by 1 desc, 3 desc
limit 10
) e
on e.residence=d.residence
group by 1,2,3
order by 1
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with by_minute_data as
(
    select 
        to_timestamp(((extract(epoch from purchase_minute)::bigint)/(60*6))*360) as six_minute,
        purchase_day,
        market,
        sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
        sum(profit) as profit,
        max(distinct_buid) as max_buid,
        min(distinct_buid) as min_buid,
        avg(distinct_buid) as avg_buid
    from
    (
        select 
            purchase_minute,
            purchase_day,
            market,
            sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
            sum(profit) as profit,
            sum(distinct_buid) as distinct_buid
        from
        (
            select 
                currency_code,
                purchase_minute,
                purchase_day,
                market,
                total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
                profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit,
                distinct_buid
            from
            (
                select
                    ta.currency_code,
                    bm.market, 
                    date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
                    date_trunc('day', purchase_time) as purchase_day,
                    sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
                    sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit,
                    count(distinct ta.binary_user_id) as distinct_buid
                from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
                on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
                left join transaction.account ta
                on ta.id= fmb.account_id
                where 
                    (purchase_time >= current_date 
                        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())) or
                    (purchase_time >= (current_date + interval'-7d') 
                        and purchase_time < (date_trunc('minute', now()) + interval '-7d')) or
                    (purchase_time >= (current_date + interval'-14d') 
                        and purchase_time < (date_trunc('minute', now()) + interval '-14d')) or
                    (purchase_time >= (current_date + interval'-21d') 
                        and purchase_time < (date_trunc('minute', now()) + interval '-21d')) or
                    (purchase_time >= (current_date + interval'-28d') 
                        and purchase_time < (date_trunc('minute', now()) + interval '-28d')) or
                    (purchase_time >= (current_date + interval'-35d') 
                        and purchase_time < (date_trunc('minute', now()) + interval '-35d'))
                group by 1,2,3,4
            ) tmp
        ) tmp2
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp3
    group by 1,2,3
)

select
  market,
  date_part('time', six_minute) as six_minute,
  purchase_day,
  --sum(amount) OVER (PARTITION BY circle_id ORDER BY ea_year, ea_month) AS cum_amt
  --sum(profit) over (partition by market order by six_minute asc rows between unbounded preceding and current row) as accumulated_profit,
  --sum(total_buy) over (partition by market order by six_minute asc rows between unbounded preceding and current row) as accumulated_buy,
  profit,
  total_buy,
  max_buid,
  min_buid,
  round(avg_buid)::bigint as avg_buid
from by_minute_data
order by 2,1"}}
name: basic stats by 6 minute intervals

 group by date(Time)
order by date(Time) DESC

{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select  deals."Symbol",
       Count(Distinct(users."Login"))   AS Total_Clients,
           
              

       SUM("Volume"/10000)  AS Total_Volume,
       SUM(("Profit")*-1)   AS Total_Profit,

   and "Symbol" IN ('Volatility 10 Index', 'Volatility 25 Index','Volatility 50 Index','Volatility 75 Index', 'Volatility 100 Index','HF Volatility 10 Index','HF Volatility 50 Index','HF Volatility 100 Index')
and date(deals."Time")<'2019-02-01'

   and users."Group" LIKE '%costarica%'
group by deals."Symbol"'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with all_rows as (
	with times as (select x as purchase_minute
				   from generate_series( {{chosen_date}}::timestamp --current_date::timestamp
					  , {{chosen_date}}::timestamp + interval '1 day' --now()::timestamp + interval '-1 minute'
					  , interval  '1 min') t(x)
	), markets as (select distinct market 
				   from bet.market
				   where market not in  ('stocks', 'legacy', 'cryptocurrency', 'futures'))

	select * from markets cross join times
	order by 2,1
)

select 
    all_rows.purchase_minute,
    all_rows.market,
    sum(coalesce(count_buy,0)) as count_buy,
    sum(coalesce(total_buy,0)) as total_buy,
    sum(coalesce(profit,0)) as profit,
    100*sum(coalesce(profit,0))/(sum(coalesce(total_buy,0))+0.001) as profit_margin
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        count_buy,
        total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy,
            sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= {{chosen_date}}::timestamp --
        and purchase_time < {{chosen_date}}::timestamp + interval '1 day' --date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2 right join all_rows
on all_rows.purchase_minute = tmp2.purchase_minute and all_rows.market = tmp2.market
group by 1,2 --rollup(2)
order by 1", 'template-tags': {'chosen_date': {'id': '15c5b447-6dcf-55d6-93fa-5d68e613af26', 'name': 'chosen_date', 'display-name': 'chosen date', 'type': 'date', 'required': True, 'default': '2019-07-01'}}}}

{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select y."Date",y."Balance Beg",y."Equity Beg",y."Floating PnL",z."Initial Deposit",z."Second Deposit",z."Withdrawals"
from 
(select to_timestamp("Datetime")::date as "Date",sum("BalancePrevDay") as "Balance Beg" , sum("EquityPrevDay") as "Equity Beg", sum("Profit") as "Floating PnL"
from mt5_daily_2019
where to_timestamp("Datetime") > '2019-01-01'
group by to_timestamp("Datetime")::date) as y
Join
(select deposit."Date",deposit."Initial Deposit",deposit."Second Deposit",withdraw."Withdrawals" from
(Select b."Date", Sum(b."Profit") Filter (Where b."row_number"=1) as "Initial Deposit",
Sum(b."Profit") Filter (Where "row_number"!=1) as "Second Deposit"
from
(select a."Time"::date as "Date","Login","Profit" ,row_number() over (partition by "Login" order by "Time") 
from
(select "Time"::date, "Login","Action","Profit"
from mt5_deals_2019
Where "Action"=2
Union
select "Time"::date, "Login","Action","Profit"
from mt5_deals_2018
Where "Action"=2
Union
select "Time"::date, "Login","Action","Profit"
from mt5_deals_2017
Where "Action"=2
Union
select "Time"::date, "Login","Action","Profit"
from mt5_deals_2016
Where "Action"=2) as a
where a."Action" =2 and a."Profit" >0) as b 
Group by b."Date") as deposit
join
 (select deals."Time"::date as "Date", sum(deals."Profit") as "Withdrawals"
 from mt5_deals_2019 as deals
 where deals."Action" =2 and deals."Profit" <0 and deals."Time" > '2019-01-01'
 Group by deals."Time"::date ) as withdraw
 on withdraw."Date"=deposit."Date" ) as z
 on y."Date"=z."Date" '}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Champion Report 1












-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

WITH 
vr AS (
    SELECT
            t.loginid,
            t.date_joined,
            ul.binary_user_id
    FROM    users.loginid ul
    JOIN    dblink('vr', $$
                SELECT bc.loginid, bc.date_joined
                FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
                WHERE bc.broker_code='VRCH'
            --    AND email NOT LIKE '%@binary.com'
            $$) AS t (loginid VARCHAR, date_joined TIMESTAMP)
                ON t.loginid = ul.loginid
    /*
        By specifying a match condition up front, PG can push that down to the foreign server and restrict the initial set rather than work against the entire table.
        This gives a result similar to creating a dblink and specifying a match condition, except we don't have the "overhead" of having to do dblink.
    */
    WHERE ul.loginid LIKE 'VRCH%'
),
cr AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT
            t.loginid,
            t.date_joined,
            t.authenticated,
            t.balance,
            t.deposit_count,
            ul.binary_user_id,
            t.first_name,
            t.last_name,
            t.email,
            t.residence,
            t.citizen
    FROM    users.loginid ul
    JOIN    dblink('cr', $$
                SELECT
                            bc.loginid,
                            bc.first_name,
                            bc.last_name,
                            bc.email,
                            bc.residence,
                            bc.citizen,
                            bc.date_joined,
                            CASE WHEN bcam.client_loginid IS NOT NULL THEN TRUE::BOOLEAN END AS authenticated,
                        -- by "converting" our value, we get consistent representation of zero balances, rather than an assortment of 0, 0.00, 0.0000
                            transaction.round_amount(ta.currency_code, ta.balance) AS balance,
                            deps.cnt AS deposit_count
                FROM        betonmarkets.client AS bc
                LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
                                SELECT DISTINCT
                                        client_loginid
                                FROM    betonmarkets.client_authentication_method
                                WHERE   client_loginid = bc.loginid
                                AND     status = 'pass'
                            ) AS bcam ON TRUE
                LEFT JOIN   transaction.account AS ta
                            ON ta.client_loginid = bc.loginid
                LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
                                SELECT COUNT(*) AS cnt
                                FROM    transaction.transaction
                                WHERE   account_id = ta.id
                                AND     action_type = 'deposit'
                            ) AS deps ON TRUE
                WHERE bc.broker_code='CH'
            $$) AS t (loginid VARCHAR, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR, residence VARCHAR, citizen VARCHAR, date_joined TIMESTAMP, authenticated BOOLEAN, balance NUMERIC, deposit_count BIGINT)
                ON t.loginid = ul.loginid
    WHERE ul.loginid LIKE 'CH%'
)
SELECT
            vr.loginid AS vr_id,
            vr.date_joined AS vr_join_date,
            cr.loginid AS real_id,
            cr.date_joined AS real_join_date,
            cr.authenticated,
            cr.balance,
            CASE WHEN cr.deposit_count > 0 THEN cr.deposit_count END AS deposit_count,
            cr.first_name,
            cr.last_name,
            cr.email,
            cr.residence,
            cr.citizen

FROM        vr
LEFT JOIN   cr
            ON cr.binary_user_id = vr.binary_user_id


ORDER BY vr.date_joined
'}}

{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT to_char(to_timestamp (M::text, 'MM'), 'TMmon') as M, Last_Date_of_month, Login, Group_, Balance 
  FROM
(SELECT
  date_part('year', to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) as Y
  ,date_part('month',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) as M
  ,to_timestamp(daily."Datetime") as Last_Date_of_month
  ,"Login" as Login
  ,"Group" as Group_
  ,daily."Balance" as Balance
  ,rank() OVER (PARTITION BY date_part('year',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")),date_part('month',to_timestamp(daily."Datetime")) ORDER BY to_timestamp(daily."Datetime") DESC) as is_day_in_month
FROM mt5_daily_2019 daily
WHERE daily."Group" NOT LIKE '%malta%') a
WHERE a.is_day_in_month =1
GROUP BY a.M, Last_Date_of_month, Login, Group_, Balance

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Snippet meant to track ICO only CR accounts. Excel will display, LoginID, Currency, Balance, Email, Last LoginDate, Account Status, Authentication Status, Corresponding accounts
select

db.*,
ull.history_date::date AS last_login_date,
array_agg(ul.loginid) AS corresponding_loginids

from

dblink('cr', $$
  select cli.binary_user_id, cli.loginid, ta.currency_code, ta.balance, cli.email, cm.authentication_method_code, array_agg(cs.status_code)
  from transaction.account AS ta
  join betonmarkets.client AS cli ON ta.client_loginid = cli.loginid
  join betonmarkets.client_status AS cs ON cs.client_loginid = ta.client_loginid
  left join betonmarkets.client_authentication_method AS cm ON cs.client_loginid = cm.client_loginid
  where cli.loginid IN (select client_loginid FROM betonmarkets.client_status where status_code = 'ico_only') 
  GROUP BY cli.binary_user_id, cli.loginid, ta.currency_code, ta.balance, cli.email, cm.authentication_method_code
$$) db (
  binary_user_id BIGINT,
  loginid VARCHAR,
  currency_code VARCHAR,
  account_balance NUMERIC,
  email VARCHAR,
  authentication_method_code VARCHAR,
  status_code VARCHAR[]
)

JOIN users.last_login_by_loginid_vw AS ull ON ull.loginid = db.loginid
JOIN users.loginid AS ul ON ul.binary_user_id = db.binary_user_id
GROUP BY db.binary_user_id, db.loginid, db.currency_code, db.account_balance, db.email, db.authentication_method_code, db.status_code, ull.history_date"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Chris > self exclusion change analysis
WITH params AS (SELECT
  'MF'::VARCHAR      AS broker_code,
  '2017-01-01'::DATE AS start_date,
  '2017-07-31'::DATE AS end_date
)

SELECT d.* FROM params, dblink(lower(params.broker_code), $$
WITH
prev AS (
SELECT DISTINCT ON (client_loginid)
    client_loginid,
    max_balance,
    max_turnover,
    max_open_bets,
    exclude_until,
    session_duration_limit,
    max_losses,
    max_7day_turnover,
    max_7day_losses,
    max_30day_turnover,
    max_30day_losses,
    timeout_until,
    last_modified_date AS last_modified
FROM audit.self_exclusion
WHERE last_modified_date < $$|| quote_literal(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified_date DESC
)
,c AS (
SELECT
    client_loginid,
    max_balance,
    max_turnover,
    max_open_bets,
    exclude_until,
    session_duration_limit,
    max_losses,
    max_7day_turnover,
    max_7day_losses,
    max_30day_turnover,
    max_30day_losses,
    timeout_until,
    last_modified_date AS last_modified
FROM audit.self_exclusion
WHERE last_modified_date >= $$|| quote_literal(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
  AND last_modified_date  < $$|| quote_literal(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1d'::INTERVAL

UNION

SELECT
    client_loginid,
    max_balance,
    max_turnover,
    max_open_bets,
    exclude_until,
    session_duration_limit,
    max_losses,
    max_7day_turnover,
    max_7day_losses,
    max_30day_turnover,
    max_30day_losses,
    timeout_until,
    last_modified_date AS last_modified
FROM betonmarkets.self_exclusion
WHERE last_modified_date >= $$|| quote_literal(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
  AND last_modified_date  < $$|| quote_literal(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1d'::INTERVAL
)

SELECT client_loginid,
    nullif(max_balance, prev_max_balance) AS max_balance,
    nullif(max_turnover, prev_max_turnover) AS max_turnover,
    nullif(max_open_bets, prev_max_open_bets) AS max_open_bets,
    nullif(exclude_until, prev_exclude_until) AS exclude_until,
    nullif(session_duration_limit, prev_session_duration_limit) AS session_duration_limit,
    nullif(max_losses, prev_max_losses) AS max_losses,
    nullif(max_7day_turnover, prev_max_7day_turnover) AS max_7day_turnover,
    nullif(max_7day_losses, prev_max_7day_losses) AS max_7day_losses,
    nullif(max_30day_turnover, prev_max_30day_turnover) AS max_30day_turnover,
    nullif(max_30day_losses, prev_max_30day_losses) AS max_30day_losses,
    to_timestamp(nullif(timeout_until, prev_timeout_until)::INTEGER) AS timeout_until,
    last_modified
FROM (
    SELECT cb.client_loginid,
	max_balance, lag(max_balance) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_balance, 
	max_turnover, lag(max_turnover) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_turnover,
	max_open_bets, lag(max_open_bets) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_open_bets,
	exclude_until, lag(exclude_until) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_exclude_until,
	session_duration_limit, lag(session_duration_limit) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_session_duration_limit,
	max_losses, lag(max_losses) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_losses,
	max_7day_turnover, lag(max_7day_turnover) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_7day_turnover,
	max_7day_losses, lag(max_7day_losses) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_7day_losses,
	max_30day_turnover, lag(max_30day_turnover) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_30day_turnover,
	max_30day_losses, lag( max_30day_losses) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_max_30day_losses,
	timeout_until, lag(timeout_until) OVER (ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified) AS prev_timeout_until,
	last_modified
    FROM (select * from prev union select * from c order by last_modified) AS cb
) AS ll
WHERE last_modified >= $$|| quote_literal(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
AND (
    max_balance IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_balance OR
    max_turnover IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_turnover OR
    max_open_bets IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_open_bets OR
    exclude_until IS DISTINCT FROM prev_exclude_until OR
    session_duration_limit IS DISTINCT FROM prev_session_duration_limit OR
    max_losses IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_losses OR
    max_7day_turnover IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_7day_turnover OR
    max_7day_losses IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_7day_losses OR
    max_30day_turnover IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_30day_turnover OR
    max_30day_losses IS DISTINCT FROM prev_max_30day_losses OR
    timeout_until IS DISTINCT FROM prev_timeout_until
)
ORDER BY client_loginid, last_modified
$$) d (
  client_loginid VARCHAR,
  max_balance NUMERIC,
  max_turnover NUMERIC,
  max_open_bets INTEGER,
  exclude_until DATE,
  session_duration_limit INTEGER,
  max_losses NUMERIC,
  max_7day_turnover NUMERIC,
  max_7day_losses NUMERIC,
  max_30day_turnover NUMERIC,
  max_30day_losses NUMERIC,
  timeout_until TEXT,
  last_modified TEXT
)"}}

{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select  to_char(deal_for_withdrawal."Time", 'DD/MM/YYYY') "date",
count(distinct deal_for_withdrawal."Login") count_user -- because a use can have multiple deposit after a withdrawal I count disint of users
from mt5_deals_2019 deal_for_withdrawal -- I used deals to find every withdrawals
inner join mt5_daily_2019 daily_balance -- I used daily table to check balance < 1$
      on to_char(deal_for_withdrawal."Time", 'DD/MM/YYYY')=TO_CHAR(TO_TIMESTAMP(daily_balance."Datetime" ), 'DD/MM/YYYY')
      and deal_for_withdrawal."Login"=daily_balance."Login"
where deal_for_withdrawal."Action"=2 
  and deal_for_withdrawal."Profit"<0 
  and daily_balance."Balance"<1
  and deal_for_withdrawal."Time"::date >  (current_date + interval '-7d')
--  and TO_TIMESTAMP(daily_balance."Datetime" )::date  (current_date + interval '-7d')
  group by to_char(deal_for_withdrawal."Time", 'DD/MM/YYYY')'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select 
case when tick_count > 0 then 'tick'
  when EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) < 60 then 'seconds'
  when ((EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) >= 60) and
    (EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) < 300)) then '1-5min'
  when ((EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) >= 300) and
    (EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) < 900)) then '5-15min'
  when ((EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) >= 900) and
    (EXTRACT(epoch FROM (expiry_time - start_time)) < 3600)) then '15min-1hour'
  else '>1hour'
  end 
as "duration_bucket",
--extract('hour' from start_time) as "start_hour",
--bm.market,
count(1)
     from bet.financial_market_bet as b
     join transaction.transaction t on b.id=t.financial_market_bet_id and t.action_type='buy' [[AND t.transaction_time >= {{purchase_since}}]]
     join transaction.account a on a.id=b.account_id
     join betonmarkets.client c on c.loginid=a.client_loginid
     left join bet.market bm on b.underlying_symbol = bm.symbol
where true [[and binary_user_id = {{binary_userid}}]]  [[and email like CONCAT({{email}}, '%')]] [[and client_loginid = {{Account_loginid}}]]
group by 1
order by count desc', 'template-tags': {'email': {'id': 'd007cfd9-042c-4e87-2e29-a8cbafe35594', 'name': 'email', 'display-name': 'Email', 'type': 'text'}, 'binary_userid': {'id': '41087f38-09bd-19dc-9a5b-baab000db31a', 'name': 'binary_userid', 'display-name': 'Binary userid', 'type': 'number'}, 'Account_loginid': {'id': '8dd49c88-20dc-037d-9ba9-b13fc67a6291', 'name': 'Account_loginid', 'display-name': 'Account loginid', 'type': 'text'}, 'purchase_since': {'id': '9db133e1-e2bd-01d5-d78f-e71588f5dbe3', 'name': 'purchase_since', 'display-name': 'Purchase since', 'type': 'date'}}}}

select 
    tmp.binary_user_id,
    tmp.client_loginid,
    tmp.transaction_time as transaction_date,
    tmp.market_type,
    tmp.currency_code,
    tmp.balance,
    bc.date_joined,
    bc.residence,
    bc.gender,
    date_part('year', age(bc.date_of_birth)) as "age"

(
    select 
        ta.binary_user_id,
        ta.client_loginid,
        transaction_time::date,
        market_type,
        currency_code,
        balance
    from transaction.firsts tf left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.id = tf.account_id
    where source in (1169,15438,15481)
    and action_type='buy'
) tmp left join betonmarkets.client bc
on bc.loginid=tmp.client_loginid'}}
