dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- This query shows the volume of open positions (Buy, Sell, Net) and the Contract size
-- POSITION_BUY 0
-- POSITION_SELL 1
-- Source: https://support.metaquotes.net/en/docs/mt5/platform/components/backup_server/sql_export/sql_mt5_positions/position_enum#enpositionaction
-- 10000 constant is defined at: https://support.metaquotes.net/en/docs/mt5/platform/components/backup_server/sql_export/sql_mt5_positions 

-- About positions:
-- A position is a trade obligation, i.e. the number of bought or sold contracts of a financial instrument. 
-- A long position is financial security bought expecting the security price go higher. 
-- A short position is an obligation to supply a security expecting the price will fall in future.

-- Source: MT5 Client help:Trading Operations / Basic Principles

SELECT 
  pos.Symbol, 
  pos.ContractSize, 
  sum(pos.Volume*(1-pos.Action))/10000 AS BUY_VOLUME, 
  sum(pos.Volume*pos.Action)/10000 AS SELL_VOLUME,
  sum(pos.Volume*(1-2*pos.Action))/10000 AS NET_VOLUME,
  sum(pos.ContractSize*pos.Volume*(1-2*pos.Action))/10000 AS NET_VALUE
FROM mt5_positions AS pos
INNER JOIN mt5_users AS users
ON pos.Login = users.login
WHERE users.Group LIKE 'real%'
AND pos.Action IN (0,1)
GROUP BY pos.Symbol
ORDER BY pos.symbol"}}
description: This query shows the volume of open positions (Buy, Sell, Net) and the Contract size
name: MT5 - Open Positions

and date(deals."Time") > '2018-12-06'
Group by date(deals."Time")
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select date_trunc('month', (Temp_table."date")), SUM (Temp_table."Profit")*-1 AS Company_BBook_Trade_Profit, SUM (Temp_table."Storage")*-1 AS Company_BBook_Swaps_Profit
FROM 
(
Select DISTINCT(ozt."order_id"), date(ozt."trade_time"), mtd."Login", mtd."Profit", mtd."Volume", mtd."Storage",  mtd."Symbol"
from mt5.oz_archive_trades_view ozt
Join mt5.mt5_deals_2018 mtd ON (ozt.order_id = (mtd."ExternalID")::integer)
where mtd."ExternalID" != ''
and ozt."trade_status" = 2 -- Trade Filled
and ozt."core_order_side" IN (1,2) -- 1 is Buy and 2 is Sell
and ozt."maker_name" = 'Warehouse') Temp_table
group by  date_trunc('month', (Temp_table."date"))
'}}
name: MT5 B-Book Profit (Match MT5 DB with OZ 'Warehouse') - Per Month

creator: {'email': 'denis.makagonov@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Denis', 'last_login': '2019-09-23T07:22:55.154Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 55, 'last_name': 'makagonov', 'date_joined': '2019-01-29T08:22:50.309Z', 'common_name': 'Denis makagonov'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select y."Date",y."Balance Beg",y."Equity Beg",y."Floating PnL",y."Closed PnL",z."Initial Deposit",z."Second Deposit",z."Withdrawals"
,y."Balance Beg"+y."Closed PnL"+z."Initial Deposit"+z."Second Deposit"+z."Withdrawals" as "Balance End"
from 
    (select 
        to_timestamp("Datetime")::date as "Date"
        ,sum("BalancePrevDay") as "Balance Beg" 
        , sum("EquityPrevDay") as "Equity Beg"
        , sum("Profit") as "Floating PnL"
        ,SUM("DailyProfit") as "Closed PnL"
    from mt5_daily_2019
    where to_timestamp("Datetime") > '2019-01-01'
    group by to_timestamp("Datetime")::date
    ) as y
Join
    (select deposit."Date"
        ,deposit."Initial Deposit"
        ,deposit."Second Deposit"
        ,withdraw."Withdrawals" 
        from
            (Select 
                b."Date"
                ,Sum(b."Profit") Filter (Where b."row_number"=1) as "Initial Deposit"
                ,Sum(b."Profit") Filter (Where "row_number"!=1) as "Second Deposit"
            from
                (select 
                    a."Time"::date as "Date"
                    ,"Login"
                    ,"Profit" 
                    ,row_number() over (partition by "Login" order by "Time") 
                from
                    (select 
                        "Time"::date
                        , "Login"
                        ,"Action"
                        ,"Profit"
                    from mt5_deals_2019
                    Where "Action"=2
                    Union
                    select 
                        "Time"::date
                        , "Login"
                        ,"Action"
                        ,"Profit"
                    from mt5_deals_2018
                    Where "Action"=2
                    Union
                    select 
                        "Time"::date
                        , "Login"
                        ,"Action"
                        ,"Profit"
                    from mt5_deals_2017
                    Where "Action"=2
                    Union
                    select 
                        "Time"::date
                        , "Login"
                        ,"Action"
                        ,"Profit"
                    from mt5_deals_2016
                    Where "Action"=2
                    ) as a
                where a."Action" =2 and a."Profit" >0
                ) as b 
            Group by b."Date"
        ) as deposit
        join
        (select 
            deals."Time"::date as "Date"
            , sum(deals."Profit") as "Withdrawals"
        from mt5_deals_2019 as deals
        where deals."Action" =2 and deals."Profit" <0 and deals."Time" > '2019-01-01'
        Group by deals."Time"::date 
        ) as withdraw
        on withdraw."Date"=deposit."Date" 
    ) as z
 on y."Date"=z."Date" '}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select -sum(w."closed_profit"+w."closed_swaps")--last(w."open_profit"::numeric+w."open_swaps"::numeric)
from (
    select 
      "Date",
      "CountDeals",
      to_timestamp("Datetime")::date as "Datetime",
      to_timestamp("DatetimePrev")::date as "DatetimePrev",
      "Login", 
      "Group", 
      "Currency", 
      "Balance",   
      "Profit" as "open_profit",
      "DailyProfit" as "closed_profit",
      "ProfitStorage" as "open_swaps",
      "DailyStorage" as "closed_swaps",
      "DailyBalance" as "deposits"
    from mt5_daily_2019
    join (
      select "Login" as "Login2", date("Time") as "Date", count(date("Time")) as "CountDeals" 
      from mt5_deals_2019 
      where {{time}}
      group by date("Time"), "Login2") as t
    on to_timestamp("Datetime")::date = t."Date" and "Login"="Login2"
    where "Balance"!="BalancePrevDay"
    and {{group}}
) as w', 'template-tags': {'time': {'widget-type': 'date/all-options', 'default': 'past30days', 'name': 'time', 'type': 'dimension', 'id': 'cb6fafc2-abaa-ad7c-a976-5a940afed56b', 'dimension': ['field-id', 7452], 'display-name': 'Time', 'required': True}, 'group': {'widget-type': 'category', 'default': 'real\costarica', 'name': 'group', 'type': 'dimension', 'id': '177da666-80b3-9283-ff6c-7b81fa5fbb0e', 'dimension': ['field-id', 7559], 'display-name': 'Group', 'required': True}}}}

dataset_query:

SELECT "Action", COUNT(*) cnt,COUNT(DISTINCT "Login") uLogins FROM mt5_deals_2018 GROUP BY "Action"
union ALL
SELECT "Action", COUNT(*) cnt,COUNT(DISTINCT "Login") uLogins FROM mt5_deals_2017 GROUP BY "Action"
union ALL
SELECT "Action", COUNT(*) cnt,COUNT(DISTINCT "Login") uLogins FROM mt5_deals_2016 GROUP BY "Action")

SELECT "Action",SUM(cnt) cnt FROM cte GROUP BY "Action"'}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT

s.Symbol AS "Symbol",
s.Description AS "Description",
s.ContractSize AS "Contract Size",
COALESCE(gs.VolumeMin, s.VolumeMin) AS "Volume Min",
COALESCE(gs.VolumeMax, s.VolumeMax) AS "Volume Max",
COALESCE(gs.VolumeStep, s.VolumeStep) AS "Volume Step",
COALESCE(gs.VolumeLimit, s.VolumeLimit) AS "Volume Limit",
s.TickSize AS "Tick Size",
s.TickValue AS "Tick Value",
COALESCE(gs.MarginInitialBuy, s.MarginInitialBuy) AS "Margin Buy",
COALESCE(gs.MarginInitialSell, s.MarginInitialSell) AS "Margin Sell",
COALESCE(gs.SwapLong, s.SwapLong) AS "Swap Long",
COALESCE(gs.SwapShort, s.SwapShort) AS "Swap Short"
FROM mt5_symbols AS s, mt5_groups_symbols AS gs, mt5_groups AS g
WHERE g.Group_ID=gs.Group_ID

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select date_trunc('month', (ozt."trade_time")),
cast(((SUM(((usd_amount)))*0.00001)) as decimal(100,3)) As LP_Commissions
from mt5.oz_archive_trades_view ozt
where date(ozt.trade_time) >= '2018-01-01'
--and  date(ozt.trade_time) <= '2018-03-31'
and ozt.order_result NOT IN (0,2) -- Ignore trades done when there are swaps or Rejected
and ozt.trade_status = 2 -- Trade Filled
and ozt."taker_mt_group" like '%vanuatu%'
and ozt.core_order_side IN (1,2) -- 1 is Buy and 2 is Sell
and ozt.maker_name NOT IN ('Warehouse','FXOpen','FXOpenUK') -- Means ignore B-Booked Trades and Trades on Cryptos
-- and ozt.taker_name != 'Warehouse' -- Means ignore Rebalancing BUT WE WILL NEED TO CONSIDER TRADES USED FOR REBALANCING 
group by date_trunc('month', (ozt."trade_time"))
'}}
name: MT5 LP Commission - Per Month

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT * from (SELECT
   users.Group AS user_group, 
   users.Login AS user_login, 
   pos.Symbol AS pos_symbol,
   sum(CASE  WHEN pos.Profit>=0 THEN pos.Volume
              WHEN pos.Profit<0 THEN -pos.Volume
          END) AS diff_volume, 
   count(pos.Profit) AS count_pos,
   sum(pos.Profit) AS total_profit
  FROM mt5_positions AS pos
  INNER JOIN mt5_users AS users
  ON (pos.Login=users.Login)
  GROUP BY users.Group, users.Login, pos.Symbol) AS t
WHERE t.diff_volume=0
ORDER BY t.user_group, t.user_login, t.pos_symbol'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select ozt.core_symbol,
cast(SUM(((maker_filled_volume))) as decimal(100,3)) As Filled_Volume,
cast(SUM(((usd_amount))) as decimal(100,3)) As Volume_in_USD,
cast(SUM(((maker_filled_volume)*(ABS(core_total_spread))*(term_ref_conversion_ratio))) as decimal(100,3)) As Spread_Revenue
from mt5.oz_trades_view ozt
where date(ozt.trade_time) >= '2018-01-01'
--and  date(ozt.trade_time) <= '2018-10-31'
and ozt.order_result NOT IN (0,2) -- Ignore trades done when there are swaps or Rejected
and ozt.trade_status = 2 -- Trade Filled
and ozt."taker_mt_group" like '%vanuatu%'
and ozt.core_order_side IN (1,2) -- 1 is Buy and 2 is Sell
and ozt.maker_name NOT IN ('Warehouse','FXOpen','FXOpenUK') -- Means ignore B-Booked Trades and Trades on Cryptos
and ozt.taker_name != 'Warehouse' -- Means ignore Rebalancing 
group by ozt.core_symbol
'}}
name: MT5 Spread Revenue - per month

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT 
date_trunc('month', CAST("mt5_deals"."Time" AS timestamp)) AS "Time"
, sum("mt5_deals"."Profit") AS "sum", sum("mt5_deals"."Profit") AS "sum"
, count(distinct "mt5_deals"."Login") AS "ActiveClients"
FROM 
(SELECT "Time","Profit","Login" FROM mt5_deals_2019
UNION all
SELECT "Time","Profit","Login" FROM mt5_deals_2018
UNION all
SELECT "Time","Profit","Login" FROM mt5_deals_2017)   as "mt5_deals"
GROUP BY date_trunc('month', CAST("mt5_deals"."Time" AS timestamp))
ORDER BY date_trunc('month', CAST("mt5_deals"."Time" AS timestamp)) ASC'}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "/*
The script is intended to output real money accounts which meet the following criteria:
a. Under a regulated landing company
b. It's been inactive (no transactions) for 6 or 10 years (based on landing company)
*/


SELECT d.*, u.all_loginids
FROM (VALUES ('mx', interval '6 years'),('mf', interval '10 years'),('mlt', interval '10 years')) AS ps (srvname, years_of_inactivity)
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$

  /*
    ta.last_modified IS NULL should indicate an account has been opened,
    but never deposited into, however some old accounts do not have it filled
    even if the account has had transactions on it. So in these cases we need
    to check the transaction.transaction table.
  */
  WITH badnulls AS (SELECT DISTINCT ta.id AS account_id, ta.client_loginid
    FROM transaction.account AS ta
    JOIN transaction.firsts AS tf ON tf.account_id=ta.id
    WHERE ta.last_modified IS NULL
    AND ta.is_default IS DISTINCT FROM false
  )

  SELECT bc.loginid AS client_loginid,
         COALESCE(tt.latest_transaction, bc.date_joined) AS last_activity,
         ta.balance AS balance,
         ta.currency_code AS currency,
         cs.status_code AS disabled,
         bc.binary_user_id AS binary_user_id
  FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
  
  LEFT JOIN transaction.account AS ta
  ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid

  LEFT JOIN badnulls ON badnulls.account_id=ta.id
  
  LEFT JOIN LATERAL(
    SELECT MAX(transaction_time) AS latest_transaction
    FROM transaction.transaction
    WHERE account_id=badnulls.account_id
  ) AS tt
  ON TRUE
   
  LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT client_loginid, status_code
    FROM betonmarkets.client_status
    WHERE status_code = 'disabled'
  ) AS cs
  ON bc.loginid = cs.client_loginid
   
  WHERE ta.is_default IS DISTINCT FROM false
  AND COALESCE(ta.last_modified, tt.latest_transaction, bc.date_joined) < current_date - $$|| quote_nullable(ps.years_of_inactivity) ||$$::INTERVAL

$$) AS d (
    client_loginid VARCHAR,
    last_activity DATE,
    balance NUMERIC,
    currency VARCHAR,
    disabled VARCHAR,
    binary_user_id BIGINT
)

LEFT JOIN dblink('users', $$
  SELECT binary_user_id, string_agg(loginid, ' ')
  FROM users.loginid
  GROUP BY binary_user_id
$$ ) AS u (
  binary_user_id BIGINT,
  all_loginids VARCHAR
) ON u.binary_user_id = d.binary_user_id
"}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "/*
The script is intended to output real money accounts which meet the following criteria:
a. Under costarica
b. Residence in eu/gb
b. It's been inactive (no transactions) for 10 years
*/


SELECT d.*, u.all_loginids
FROM dblink('cr', $$

/*
ta.last_modified IS NULL should indicate an account has been opened,
but never deposited into, however some old accounts do not have it filled
even if the account has had transactions on it. So in these cases we need
to check the transaction.transaction table.
*/
WITH badnulls AS (SELECT DISTINCT ta.id AS account_id, ta.client_loginid
  FROM transaction.account AS ta
  JOIN transaction.firsts AS tf ON tf.account_id=ta.id
  WHERE ta.last_modified IS NULL
  AND ta.is_default IS DISTINCT FROM false
),

ps as(select * from (VALUES
  (ARRAY['gb','im','es','pt','cz','lu','bg','hu','lt','lv','de','gr','si','it','hr','sk','fi','dk','fr','cy','pl','mf','ie','ee','nl','be','se','ro','at'], interval '10 years')
) ps (residences, years_of_inactivity))

SELECT bc.loginid AS client_loginid,
        bc.residence AS residence,
         COALESCE(ta.last_modified, tt.latest_transaction, bc.date_joined) AS last_activity,
         ta.balance AS balance,
         ta.currency_code AS currency,
         cs.status_code AS disabled,
         bc.binary_user_id AS binary_user_id
  FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
  
  LEFT JOIN transaction.account AS ta
  ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
  
  LEFT JOIN badnulls ON badnulls.account_id=ta.id

  LEFT JOIN LATERAL(
    SELECT MAX(transaction_time) AS latest_transaction
    FROM transaction.transaction
    WHERE account_id=badnulls.account_id
  ) AS tt
  ON TRUE
   
  LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT client_loginid, status_code
    FROM betonmarkets.client_status
    WHERE status_code = 'disabled'
  ) AS cs
  ON bc.loginid = cs.client_loginid
CROSS JOIN ps
  WHERE ta.is_default IS DISTINCT FROM false
  AND bc.residence = ANY(ps.residences::VARCHAR[])
  AND COALESCE(ta.last_modified, tt.latest_transaction, bc.date_joined) < current_date - ps.years_of_inactivity

$$) AS d (
  client_loginid VARCHAR,
  residence VARCHAR,
  last_activity DATE,
  balance NUMERIC,
  currency VARCHAR,
  disabled VARCHAR,
  binary_user_id BIGINT
)

LEFT JOIN dblink('users', $$
 SELECT binary_user_id, string_agg(loginid, ' ') AS all_loginids
 FROM users.loginid
 GROUP BY binary_user_id
$$ ) AS u (
 binary_user_id BIGINT,
 all_loginids VARCHAR
) ON u.binary_user_id = d.binary_user_id"}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- CR/MT5 CRS report .v4
WITH mt AS (
	-- this CTE can be run by itself to see the raw MT5 results
	SELECT mtu."Login", mtu."Registration", mtd."Balance", mtd."Currency", deals."profit", deals."swap", deals."eod_profit", deals."eod_swap", deals."eod_commission", deals."eod_correction"
	FROM mt5.mt5_users AS mtu
	JOIN (
		SELECT		-- This yields one row for every Login id who did something that created a record in deal
		  "login",
			SUM("profit")  FILTER (WHERE "action" IN (0,1) AND "entry"=1) AS profit,	-- Only add up BUY/SELL
			SUM("storage") FILTER (WHERE "action" IN (0,1) AND "entry"=1) AS swap,
		-- The following sub sets are only necessary to adjust closing balance figures
			SUM("profit")     FILTER (WHERE "time" > '2017-12-31 21:00:59' AND "action" IN (0,1) AND "entry"=1) AS eod_profit,	-- Only add up BUY/SELL records that were not reflected in the last day's final sums
			SUM("storage")    FILTER (WHERE "time" > '2017-12-31 21:00:59' AND "action" IN (0,1) AND "entry"=1) AS eod_swap,
			SUM("commission") FILTER (WHERE "time" > '2017-12-31 21:00:59' AND "action" IN (0,1) AND "entry"=1) AS eod_commission,
			SUM("profit")     FILTER (WHERE "time" > '2017-12-31 21:00:59' AND "action"=5)                    AS eod_correction	-- Only add up corrections records that were not reflected in the last day's final sums
		FROM mt5.deals_2017 deal		-- this is a static local table copied directly from MT5 to speed up the process
		GROUP BY "login"
	) AS deals ON deals."login"=mtu."Login"
	LEFT JOIN mt5.mt5_daily_2017 AS mtd	-- unfortunately some clients have no entry in here, so LEFT JOIN
		ON mtd."Login"=mtu."Login"
		AND mtd."Datetime" = 1514754059	-- Sunday, December 31, 2017 10:00:59 PM (Last date/time in the mt5_daily_2017 table)
	WHERE mtu."Group" LIKE '%real\\vanuatu%'
)

SELECT
	cr.cr_loginid, cr.mt5_loginid,
	mt."Registration" AS mt_acct_opening_date,
	'Other'::VARCHAR AS account_type,
	client.status AS account_status, client.first_name, client.last_name,
	bbc.country_name AS country_of_residence,
	UPPER(client.tax_residence) AS tax_residence,
	client.tax_identification_number,
	client.date_of_birth,
	UPPER(client.place_of_birth) AS place_of_birth, 
	client.address_line_1, client.address_line_2, client.address_postcode, client.address_city, client.address_state,
	UPPER(client.residence) AS residence,
	transaction.round_amount(mt."Currency", mt."Balance"::NUMERIC) AS account_balance,
	mt."Currency" AS account_currency,
	transaction.round_amount(mt."Currency", mt."profit"::NUMERIC) AS profit,
	transaction.round_amount(mt."Currency", mt."swap"::NUMERIC) AS swap,
	transaction.round_amount(mt."Currency", mt."eod_profit"::NUMERIC) AS eod_profit,
	transaction.round_amount(mt."Currency", mt."eod_swap"::NUMERIC) AS eod_swap,
	cr.binary_user_id
FROM mt
JOIN oldest_cr_sibling_mt AS cr
	ON cr.mt5_loginid='MT'||mt."Login"::VARCHAR
JOIN LATERAL (
	-- This part is the clientDB part. Rather than grabbing every client and filtering them in reportDB, we are grabbing only the ones of interest.
	SELECT * FROM dblink('cr', $$
		SELECT
			bc.first_name, bc.last_name, bc.residence, bc.tax_residence, bc.tax_identification_number, bc.date_of_birth, bc.place_of_birth, 
			bc.address_line_1, bc.address_line_2, bc.address_postcode, bc.address_city, bc.address_state,
			cs.status
		FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
		LEFT JOIN LATERAL (
			SELECT string_agg(bcs.status_code, ', ') AS status
              FROM betonmarkets.client_status AS bcs
             WHERE bcs.client_loginid = bc.loginid
               AND bcs.status_code IN ('disabled','unwelcome','cashier_locked')
		) AS cs ON TRUE
		WHERE bc.loginid= $$|| quote_literal(cr.cr_loginid) ||$$
	$$) AS cr (
		first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, residence VARCHAR, tax_residence VARCHAR, tax_identification_number VARCHAR, date_of_birth VARCHAR, place_of_birth VARCHAR,
		address_line_1 VARCHAR, address_line_2 VARCHAR, address_postcode VARCHAR, address_city VARCHAR, address_state VARCHAR, status VARCHAR
	)
) AS client ON TRUE
-- This is a local, static table created from the countries.yml file
JOIN brands_binary_countries AS bbc
	ON bbc.country_code=client.residence
WHERE bbc.tax_details_required
ORDER BY 2'}}
name: mt5_jackdb_CR/MT5 CRS report .v4

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select ozt.core_symbol,
cast(SUM(((maker_filled_volume))) as decimal(100,3)) As Filled_Volume,
cast(SUM(((usd_amount))) as decimal(100,3)) As Volume_in_USD,
cast(SUM(((maker_filled_volume)*(ABS(core_total_spread))*(term_ref_conversion_ratio))) as decimal(100,3)) As Spread_Revenue
from mt5.oz_trades_view ozt
where date(ozt.trade_time) >= '2018-01-01'
--and  date(ozt.trade_time) <= '2018-10-31'
and ozt.order_result NOT IN (0,2) -- Ignore trades done when there are swaps or Rejected
and ozt.trade_status = 2 -- Trade Filled
and ozt."taker_mt_group" like '%vanuatu%'
and ozt.core_order_side IN (1,2) -- 1 is Buy and 2 is Sell
and ozt.maker_name NOT IN ('Warehouse','FXOpen','FXOpenUK') -- Means ignore B-Booked Trades and Trades on Cryptos
and ozt.taker_name != 'Warehouse' -- Means ignore Rebalancing 
group by ozt.core_symbol
'}}

creator: {'email': 'parviz@regentmarkets.com', 'first_name': 'Parviz', 'last_login': '2019-07-03T05:55:34.855Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': False, 'id': 52, 'last_name': 'asoodefard', 'date_joined': '2019-01-08T07:10:52.493Z', 'common_name': 'Parviz asoodefard'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select  c.binary_user_id,
        c.loginid, -- the key of betonmarket.client
        --c.email,
        c.date_joined,
        frst.first_trade,
        frst.first_deposit,
        mnt.yearmonth,
        mnt.account_id,   --account_id_in_transaction.account,
        mnt.finansial_turnover,
        mnt.finansial_revenue,
        mnt.volindx_turnover,
        mnt.volindx_revenue
from betonmarkets.client c
left join transaction.account a
  on a.client_loginid = c.loginid
left join (select YearMonth,
                  account_id,
                  sum(case when market = 'Finansial' then Turnover else 0 end) Finansial_Turnover,
                  sum(case when market = 'Finansial' then Revenue else 0 end) Finansial_Revenue,
                  sum(case when market = 'Volindx' then Turnover else 0 end) Volindx_Turnover,
                  sum(case when market = 'Volindx' then Revenue else 0 end) Volindx_Revenue
          from (select  to_char(f.purchase_time,'YYYY-MM') YearMonth,
                        f.account_id,
                        case when left(f.underlying_symbol,1)='R' then 'Volindx' else 'Finansial' end market,
                        sum(f.buy_price) Turnover,
                        sum(f.sell_price - f.buy_price) Revenue
                from bet.financial_market_bet f
                where  purchase_time >= '2018-01-01'--current_date + interval '-1d'
               			and purchase_time < '2019-01-01'--current_date
                group by to_char(f.purchase_time,'YYYY-MM') ,
                        f.account_id,
                        case when left(f.underlying_symbol,1)='R' then 'Volindx' else 'Finansial' end) ag
          group by  YearMonth,
                    account_id) mnt
  on mnt.account_id=a.id
left join (select account_id,
                  max(case when action_type='trade' then trans_date end) first_trade,
                  max(case when action_type='deposit' then trans_date end) first_deposit
          from (select  account_id,
                        case when action_type <> 'deposit' then 'trade' else 'deposit' end action_type, --because I didn't wanted use OR operation (awful performance) and with knowledge we put withdrawal away I put this condition
                        min(transaction_time) trans_date
                from transaction.firsts
                where action_type <> 'withdrawal' --another way to write: in ('deposit','sell','buy')
                group by account_id,
                        case when action_type <> 'deposit' then 'trade' else 'deposit' end) first_action
          group by account_id)frst
on frst.account_id=a.id

where c.date_joined >= '2018-01-01'
and   c.date_joined <  '2019-01-01'"}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select CAST(transaction_time AS date), --action_type, market_type, sum(amount), count(amount)
--/*
count(1) filter(where action_type='deposit') as num_first_deposits, 
coalesce(sum(amount) filter (where action_type='deposit'), 0) as first_deposits_amount, 
count(1) filter(where action_type='buy' and market_type='financial') as num_first_financial_buy,
coalesce(sum(abs(amount)) filter(where action_type='buy' and market_type='financial'), 0) as amount_first_financial_buy,
count(1) filter(where action_type='buy' and market_type !='financial') as num_first_nonfinancial_buy,
coalesce(sum(abs(amount)) filter(where action_type='buy' and market_type !='financial'), 0) as amount_first_nonfinancial_buy
--*/
from transaction.firsts
WHERE CAST(transaction_time AS date) BETWEEN CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-42 day') AS date)
   AND CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-1 day') AS date)
--and action_type in ('deposit', 'buy')
GROUP BY 1 --,2,3
ORDER BY CAST(transaction_time AS date) DESC--, action_type, market_type
limit 42"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- New Registrations, New Real Accounts, First Deposits, New Active Accounts
WITH const (itv) as (
  values ('350 days'::interval)
)

select na.date_joined,total_new_virtual,total_new_real,total_new_real_deposited,total_new_real_deposited_traded from 
(-- new virtual --
select date_joined, count(distinct binary_user_id) as "total_new_virtual"
from quants.client_summary_mv, const
where date_joined >= NOW()-itv
--and residence = 'id'--
and broker_code = 'VRTC'
group by date_joined) as nv

full outer join (-- new real --
select date_joined, count(distinct binary_user_id) as "total_new_real"
from quants.client_summary_mv, const
where date_joined >= NOW()-itv
--and residence = 'id'--
and broker_code = 'CR'
group by date_joined) as na

on na.date_joined = nv.date_joined
full outer join (
-- new real that deposited money --
select fd_transaction_date, count(distinct binary_user_id) as "total_new_real_deposited"
from quants.client_summary_mv, const
where date_joined >= NOW()-itv
--and residence = 'id'--
and broker_code = 'CR'
and fd_amount_usd is not null
group by fd_transaction_date) as nad

on nad.fd_transaction_date = na.date_joined
full outer join (
-- new real that deposited money and traded --
select fb_transaction_date, count(distinct binary_user_id) as "total_new_real_deposited_traded"
from quants.client_summary_mv, const
where date_joined >= NOW()-itv
--and residence = 'id'--
and broker_code = 'CR'
and fd_amount_usd is not null
and fb_amount_usd is not null
group by fb_transaction_date
) as nadt
on nadt.fb_transaction_date = nad.fd_transaction_date

'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- This query returns information about most recent sign-up clients, such as loginID, Client ID, Date of Join, Deposit Amount,  Cumulative Deposits , Trading activity on demo (YES/NO), Country, email
SELECT a.loginid "Login ID", 
f.firstname "First Name",
f.lastname "Last Name",
a.date_joined "Date Joined", 
a.fd_amount_usd "First Deposit(USD)", 
a.fd_transaction_date "First Deposit Date", 
a.residence "Country", 
b.email "Email", 

CASE WHEN binary_user_id IN 
(select binary_user_id from quants.client_summary_mv 
where date_joined <= NOW()
and broker_code = 'VRTC'
and fb_amount_usd is not NULL) THEN 'Yes'

WHEN binary_user_id IN (select binary_user_id from quants.client_summary_mv 
where date_joined <= NOW()
and broker_code = 'VRTC'
and fb_amount_usd is NULL) THEN 'No'

Else 'No virtual A/c'
End
"Demo Trade",
c.sum "Acc Deposit", 
d.amount "Last Deposit", 
d.time "Last Deposit Time"
from users.binary_user b, quants.client_summary_mv a 

left join 
(select * from dblink('cr', $$
select a.client_loginid, sum(p.amount*e.rate)
  from payment.payment p
  join transaction.account a on a.id=p.account_id
  left join data_collection.exchangeToUSD_rate(a.currency_code, p.payment_time) e on true
 where p.amount>0
   and p.payment_time >= '2018-01-01'
 group by 1
$$) t(loginid varchar, sum numeric)) as c 
on a.loginid = c.loginid

left join
(select * from dblink('cr', $$
select a.client_loginid, p.amount*e.rate, p.payment_time
  from payment.payment p
  join transaction.account a on a.id=p.account_id
  left join data_collection.exchangeToUSD_rate(a.currency_code, p.payment_time) e on true
 where p.amount > 0
   and p.payment_time >= '2018-01-01'
   and p.payment_time in (SELECT max(p2.payment_time) FROM payment.payment p2 WHERE p.account_id = p2.account_id
   and p2.amount > 0)
$$) t(loginid varchar, amount numeric, time timestamp)) as d
on c.loginid = d.loginid

Left join
(select * from dblink('cr', $$
select loginid, first_name, last_name
  from audit.client
  where operation = 'INSERT'
$$) t(loginid varchar, firstname varchar, lastname varchar)) as f
on d.loginid = f.loginid

where a.binary_user_id = b.id
and a.date_joined >= NOW()-'2 day'::interval
and a.fd_amount_usd is not NULL
and a.broker_code = 'CR'
order by a.date_joined DESC

-- Created by Stanly
'}}

dataset_query:
{'native': {'query': 'select source, tmp."has_token",
count(distinct tmp.binary_user_id) 
from
(
    select
        bc.loginid,
        bc.binary_user_id,
        ta.id as "tr_id",
        case coalesce(bc.myaffiliates_token, '') when '' then false else true end as "has_token"
    from betonmarkets.client bc left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.client_loginid=bc.loginid
    where residence in ('ng', 'ru', 'za')
    and age(date_of_birth) >= interval '41 year'
    and age(date_of_birth) <= interval '65 year'
) tmp inner join transaction.transaction tt
on tt.account_id=tmp."tr_id"
where transaction_time >= '2019-01-01'
and transaction_time < '2019-02-01'
and action_type='buy'
group by 1,2

WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 25 Index' THEN deals."Profit"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.5
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 50 Index' THEN deals."Profit"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.5
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 75 Index' THEN deals."Profit"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.01

WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 100 Index' THEN deals."Profit"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.3

CASE
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 10 Index' THEN deals."Storage"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.1
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 25 Index' THEN deals."Storage"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.5
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 50 Index' THEN deals."Storage"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.5
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 75 Index' THEN deals."Storage"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.01
WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 100 Index' THEN deals."Storage"/(deals."Volume"/10000)*0.01

from
(
    select a.*, bc.residence, data_collection.exchangetousd_rate("currency_code", "date") as "exchange_rate"
    from
    (
        select tf.amount, tf.transaction_time::date as "date", ta.client_loginid, ta.currency_code from transaction.firsts tf left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id=tf.account_id
        where tf.action_type = 'deposit'
        and transaction_time >= (now() + interval '-7 day')::timestamp::date
        and transaction_time < now()::timestamp::date
    ) as a left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on a."client_loginid" = bc.loginid
) b
where residence in ('id', 'br', 'mx', 'th', 'za', 
                    'in', 'ng', 'bo', 'tw', 'vn', 
                    'ru', 'ua', 'do', 'lk', 'ke', 
                    'bd', 'uy', 'au', 'kz', 'co')
group by 1,2
order by 2 desc, 4 desc

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- oauth.apps history by App ID
-- The report will show all the history for a particular app ID. Top record is current state.
-- Note: we did not start recording changes until late 2016, so changes prior to that are not recorded.
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '1439'::BIGINT AS id 
)







-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE
SELECT
  t.id AS "APP ID",
  t.app_name,
  t.binary_user_id,
  t.stamp AS date_this_went_into_effect,
  t.active,
  t.app_markup_percentage,
  t.homepage,
  t.scopes,
  t.appstore
FROM params, dblink('auth', 'SELECT id, name, binary_user_id, stamp::TIMESTAMP(0), active, app_markup_percentage, homepage, scopes, appstore FROM oauth.apps WHERE id='|| params.id ||''::TEXT)
  t (id TEXT, app_name TEXT, binary_user_id TEXT, stamp TEXT, active TEXT, app_markup_percentage TEXT, homepage TEXT, scopes TEXT, appstore TEXT)

UNION ALL

SELECT
  ex.id AS "App ID",
  ex.name AS app_name,
  ex.binary_user_id,
  to_char(ex.stamp, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS'::TEXT)::TEXT  AS date_in_effect,
  ex.active,
  ex.app_markup_percentage,
  ex.homepage,
  ex.scopes,
  ex.appstore
FROM params, dblink('auth', 'SELECT data FROM oauth.apps_archive WHERE id='|| params.id ||' ORDER BY archival_stamp DESC'::TEXT) ta (data jsonb)
JOIN LATERAL jsonb_to_record(ta.data) ex (
  name TEXT,
  homepage TEXT,
  github TEXT,
  appstore TEXT,
  googleplay TEXT,
  binary_user_id TEXT,
  active TEXT,
  redirect_uri TEXT,
  scopes TEXT,
  id TEXT,
  app_markup_percentage TEXT,
  stamp TIMESTAMP) ON TRUE'}}
description: oauth.apps history by App ID

      sum(tmp."total_buy")*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date) as "total_buy_USD_now",
      sum(tmp."potential_max_payout")*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date) as "potential_max_payout_USD_now",
      sum(tmp."count_contracts") as "count_contracts"
    from
        (
        select
          account_id,
          underlying_symbol,
          sum(buy_price) as "total_buy",
          sum(payout_price) as "potential_max_payout",
          count(1) as "count_contracts"
        from bet.financial_market_bet_open
        group by 1,2
        ) tmp
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id = tmp.account_id
    group by 1,2
) tmp2
where substring(tmp2.underlying_symbol from 1 for 1) = 'R'
group by 1
order by 3 desc, 2
limit 30'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- P&L by broker code for interval
-- The initial intention for this report is to be used as a spreadsheet to be joined with other spreadsheets in order to provide this P&L by loginid
WITH params AS (SELECT
-- CH, CR, MF, MX, MLT, JP...
-- bear in mind that running against CR will produce a very large report that will probably take "forever" to run without a tight interval
	'MF'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,

-- Leave the following AS NULL::DATE to get the P&L from account opening until the end_date
-- otherwise specify a date like this: '2018-01-01'::DATE
	NULL::DATE AS start_date,
	'2018-03-31'::DATE AS end_date
)

-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink (ps.srvname, $$
	SELECT bc.loginid,
		ta.currency_code,
		SUM(tt.amount) AS profit_loss
	FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
	JOIN transaction.account AS ta
	     ON ta.client_loginid = bc.loginid
	JOIN transaction.transaction AS tt
	     ON tt.account_id = ta.id
	WHERE 
	    bc.broker_code = $$|| quote_literal(params.broker_code) ||$$
	AND tt.action_type IN ('buy','sell')
	AND tt.transaction_time >= $$|| quote_literal( COALESCE(params.start_date, '2000-01-01') ) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
	AND tt.transaction_time < $$|| quote_nullable( params.end_date ) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
	GROUP BY 1,2
	ORDER BY betonmarkets.loginid_sortable(bc.loginid)
$$) AS dbl(
	loginid VARCHAR,
	currency_code VARCHAR,
	profit_loss NUMERIC
)
WHERE params.broker_code = ANY(ps.broker_codes);
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with all_rows as (
	with times as (select x as purchase_minute
				   from generate_series(date_trunc('minute', now() + interval '-4 hour') --current_date::timestamp
					  , date_trunc('minute', now() + interval '-1m')::timestamp
					  , interval  '1 min') t(x)
	), markets as (select distinct market 
				   from bet.market
				   where market not in  ('stocks', 'legacy', 'cryptocurrency', 'futures'))

	select * from markets cross join times
	order by 2,1
)

select 
    all_rows.purchase_minute,
    all_rows.market,
    sum(coalesce(count_buy,0)) as count_buy
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        count_buy
        --total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        --profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy
            --sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            --sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= now() + interval '-24h' --current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2 right join all_rows
on all_rows.purchase_minute = tmp2.purchase_minute and all_rows.market = tmp2.market
group by 1,2"}}
name: Past 4 hours: Count of purchased contracts, by the minute

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with all_rows as (
	with times as (select x as purchase_minute
				   from generate_series(date_trunc('minute', now() + interval '-1 hour') --current_date::timestamp
					  , date_trunc('minute', now() + interval '-1m')::timestamp
					  , interval  '1 min') t(x)
	), markets as (select distinct market 
				   from bet.market
				   where market not in  ('stocks', 'legacy', 'cryptocurrency', 'futures'))

	select * from markets cross join times
	order by 2,1
)

select 
    all_rows.purchase_minute,
    all_rows.market,
    sum(coalesce(count_buy,0)) as count_buy
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        count_buy
        --total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        --profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy
            --sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            --sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= now() + interval '-24 hour' --current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2 right join all_rows
on all_rows.purchase_minute = tmp2.purchase_minute and all_rows.market = tmp2.market
group by 1,2"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
  xyz."payment_date",
  sum(xyz."exchange_rate" * xyz."amount") as "deposit_amount_USD",
  sum(xyz."count") as "deposit_count"
from
(
    select data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(abc."currency_code", abc."payment_date"::timestamp) as "exchange_rate", abc.*
    from
    (
        select
          ta.currency_code,
          payment_time::timestamp::date as "payment_date",
          sum(amount) as "amount",
          count(1) as "count" 
        from payment.payment pp left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id=pp.account_id
        where payment_time >= (now() + interval '-30 day')::timestamp::date
        and payment_time < now()::timestamp::date
        and payment_gateway_code = 'payment_agent_transfer'
        and amount > 0
        group by 1,2
    ) abc
) xyz
group by 1
order by 1
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with numbers as
(select count(purchase_time) filter (where tick_count is not null) as tick_contract, 
 		count(purchase_time) as total_contract,
 		count (distinct fmb.account_id) filter (where tick_count is not null) as tick_user,
 		count (distinct fmb.account_id) as total_user
 from bet.financial_market_bet as fmb 
 join transaction.transaction as t 
 on fmb.id = t.financial_market_bet_id 
 where purchase_time > now() -'7days'::interval  and source in (10,14473) ) 

select  tick_contract,
		total_contract, 
		round(100*tick_contract/total_contract,2) as percentage_contract,
		tick_user,
		total_user, 
		round(100*tick_user/total_user,2) as percentage_user
from numbers 
"}}
name: Percentage contracts and users of mobile user trade with tick contracts

loginid,
t.currency_code,
first_name,
last_name,
email,
residence,
--citizen,
date_joined
from audit.client
join transaction.account t on loginid = t.client_loginid
where date_joined >= NOW()-'1 day'::interval
and t.currency_code = 'EUR'
--and citizen <> ''
and residence in ('pk', 'bd')
--and date_joined >= NOW()-'30 day'::interval
group by 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7
order by date_joined desc
limit 100"}}

dataset_query:
{'native': {'template-tags': {'date_string': {'id': '1214e187-7e57-f9bb-bcac-518deb1ae151', 'name': 'date_string', 'display-name': 'enter a date', 'type': 'date', 'required': True, 'default': '2019-05-04'}, 'first_letter': {'id': 'd1f24ec6-de99-4b13-e182-a63c4c469861', 'name': 'first_letter', 'display-name': 'First Letter', 'type': 'text', 'required': True, 'default': 'f'}}, 'query': "select
    hour_of_day,
    sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
    sum(total_profit) as total_profit
from
(
    select 
        tmp.account_id,
        tmp.hour_of_day,
        tmp.total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date) as total_buy,
        tmp.total_profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, now()::date) as total_profit
    from
    (
        select 
            account_id, 
            date_part('hour', purchase_time) as hour_of_day, 
            sum(coalesce(buy_price,0)) as total_buy, 
            sum(coalesce(buy_price,0) - coalesce(sell_price,0)) as total_profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet 
        where purchase_time >= {{date_string}}::date
        and purchase_time < {{date_string}}::date + interval '1d'
        and substr(underlying_symbol,1,1)={{first_letter}}
        --current_date --+ interval '-2d'
        group by 1, 2
    ) tmp 
    left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.id=tmp.account_id
) tmp2
group by 1"}, 'type': 'native', 'database': 2}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select tmp2.source, tmp.* from
(
select
  fmb.id as fmb_id,
  ta.client_loginid,
  purchase_time,
  underlying_symbol,
  round(payout_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time),2) as "payout_usd",
  round(buy_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time),2) as "buy_usd",
  round(sell_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time),2) as "sell_usd",
  start_time,
  expiry_time,
  remark,
  short_code,
  tick_count,
  currency_code,
  data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time) as "Exchange_Rate"
from bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join transaction.account ta
on ta.id=fmb.account_id
where purchase_time >= current_date + interval '-7d' --'2019-03-27'
and purchase_time < current_date --'2019-03-28'
--and buy_price*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time) >= 100.0
) tmp left join 
(
select * from
transaction.transaction
where action_type='buy'
and transaction_time >= current_date + interval '-7d' + interval '-10m'
and transaction_time < current_date
) tmp2

on tmp.fmb_id=tmp2.financial_market_bet_id
limit 10'}}

        -- CR, MX, MLT, MF or VR
        'MF1386'::VARCHAR as login_id,

        -- Start date
        '2016-07-03'::TIMESTAMP as start_date,

        -- End date
        '2016-09-13'::TIMESTAMP as end_date
)









-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE
SELECT * FROM get_client_trades_details(
    (SELECT broker_code FROM param)::varchar,
    (SELECT login_id FROM param)::varchar,
    (SELECT start_date FROM param)::timestamp,
    (SELECT end_date FROM param)::timestamp
    );
"}}

WITH param as (
    SELECT
        -- CR, MX, MLT, MF or VR
        'CR'::VARCHAR as broker_code,
        
        -- CR, MX, MLT, MF or VR
        'CR299974'::VARCHAR as login_id,

        -- Start date
        '2015-07-03'::TIMESTAMP as start_date,

        -- End date
        '2015-07-07'::TIMESTAMP as end_date
)









-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE
SELECT * FROM get_client_trades_details(
    (SELECT broker_code FROM param)::varchar,
    (SELECT login_id FROM param)::varchar,
    (SELECT start_date FROM param)::timestamp,
    (SELECT end_date FROM param)::timestamp
    );
"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Quants > Get news since date
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2017-08-17'::DATE AS start_date,
  
  -- specify one or symbol/s like this "JPY","AUD"
  -- -or- just remove any symbols to get all symbols '{  }'...
  '{ "JPY" }'::VARCHAR[] AS symbols
),




-- no adjustments needed below


SELECT t.source,
       t.event_name,
       t.symbol,
       t.release_date::VARCHAR AS release_epoch,
       to_timestamp(t.release_date::bigint)::TIMESTAMP::TEXT AS release_date,
       t.id,
       t.recorded_date::VARCHAR AS recorded_epoch,
       to_timestamp(t.recorded_date::bigint)::TIMESTAMP::TEXT AS recorded_date
  FROM params p
 CROSS JOIN chronicle c
 CROSS JOIN json_populate_recordset(null::chronicle_economic_event, c.value::json#>'{events}') AS t
 WHERE c.category='economic_events'
   AND c."timestamp" >= p.start_date
   AND array_length(p.symbols, 1) IS NULL

UNION ALL

SELECT t.source,
       t.event_name,
       t.symbol,
       t.release_date::VARCHAR AS release_epoch,
       to_timestamp(t.release_date::bigint)::TIMESTAMP::TEXT AS release_date,
       t.id,
       t.recorded_date::VARCHAR AS recorded_epoch,
       to_timestamp(t.recorded_date::bigint)::TIMESTAMP::TEXT AS recorded_date
  FROM params p
 CROSS JOIN chronicle c
 CROSS JOIN json_populate_recordset(null::chronicle_economic_event, c.value::json#>'{events}') AS t
 WHERE c.category='economic_events'
   AND c."timestamp" >= p.start_date
   AND t.symbol = ANY(p.symbols);
'}}
description: Quants > Get news since date
name: Quants Get news since date

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Search login history by client_loginid or binary_user_id for history beginning June 2015
-- Quants -> login history
-- Below you can use one or the other of the parameters. I would not suggest using none as that will give you all 3M+ rows ;-)
-- If you use just the binary_user_id, you will get all logins across all client_loginids for that binary account
-- If you use just the client_loginid I think you know what you will get ;-)
-- Don't use both as it will be too easy to end up with an empty result
-- The unused one should be an uncommented NULL. Just switch your comments (--) around to use either one and leave the other NULL
-- If you get an error, make sure two and two only of the parameter lines are uncommented.
WITH params AS (SELECT
  --4086586::BIGINT AS binary_user_id,
  NULL::BIGINT AS binary_user_id,
  --'CR478849'::VARCHAR AS client_loginid
  NULL::VARCHAR AS client_loginid
)

-- Don't change any code below here

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN LATERAL dblink('users', $$
SELECT
  loginid,
  binary_user_id,
  action,
  history_date,
  environment,
  successful
FROM users.login_history_by_loginid_vw
WHERE TRUE
$$|| CASE WHEN params.binary_user_id IS NOT NULL THEN ('AND binary_user_id = '|| quote_literal(params.binary_user_id))::TEXT ELSE '' END ||$$
$$|| CASE WHEN params.client_loginid IS NOT NULL THEN ('AND loginid = '|| quote_literal(params.client_loginid))::TEXT ELSE '' END ||$$
ORDER BY history_date DESC$$)
dbl ( loginid TEXT,
      binary_user_id BIGINT,
      action TEXT,
      history_date TEXT,
      environment TEXT,
      successful BOOLEAN)"}}
description: Search login history by client_loginid or binary_user_id for history beginning June 2015
name: Quants login history

SELECT
  *, timestamp at time zone 'UTC' as ts
 FROM
  chronicle 
 WHERE
  category='volatility_surfaces' 
  AND name='frxEURUSD' 
  AND timestamp at time zone 'UTC' > '2016-02-16T10:00:00'
  AND timestamp at time zone 'UTC' < '2016-02-16T15:00:00'
 ORDER BY
  timestamp DESC"}}

name: Query historical volatility surface

*/"}}

WHERE CAST("bet"."daily_aggregates"."day" AS date) BETWEEN CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-30 day') AS date)
   AND CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-1 day') AS date)
order by abs(loss) desc, "day" desc, "percentage loss" desc
limit 20

dataset_query:
{'native': {'template-tags': {'country1': {'id': 'f4118d27-1410-6e46-2563-09fcbff2632b', 'name': 'country1', 'display-name': 'Country1', 'type': 'text', 'required': True, 'default': 'in'}, 'country2': {'id': '18843c2a-9840-421d-85b1-48aaed05f015', 'name': 'country2', 'display-name': 'Country2', 'type': 'text', 'required': True, 'default': 'ru'}, 'country3': {'id': 'adc9aa30-36f9-d56c-3c93-7b69f18c6a6a', 'name': 'country3', 'display-name': 'Country3', 'type': 'text', 'required': True, 'default': 'ua'}}, 'query': 'select 
sss.residence, sss.client_loginid, sum(sss.total_buy) as "total_buy", sum(sss.company_revenue) as "company_revenue"
from
(
    select bc.residence, ttt.* from
    (
        select 
        a.client_loginid,
        tmp.account_id,
        tmp.market,
        round(tmp.total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "total_buy",
        round(tmp.company_revenue*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "company_revenue"
        from
            (
            select 
                account_id,
                bm.market,
                cast(purchase_time as date) as "day", 
                sum(buy_price) as "total_buy",
                sum((buy_price - sell_price)) as "company_revenue"
            from bet.financial_market_bet fmb
            left join bet.market bm
            on bm.symbol=fmb.underlying_symbol
            where purchase_time >= now() + INTERVAL '-4 hour'
            --and market='forex'    
            and is_sold = TRUE
            group by 1,2,3 
        ) tmp
            left join transaction.account a
            on tmp.account_id=a.id
    ) ttt left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on bc.loginid=ttt.client_loginid
) sss
where residence in ({{country1}}, {{country2}}, {{country3}})
and abs(company_revenue) > 50
group by 1,2
order by 4, 3
'}, 'type': 'native', 'database': 2}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "WITH param(uk_or_not_uk) AS (VALUES (
    true  -- true or false
))

-- dont change below
, users as (
    select * from dblink('users',
        $$
        select l1.loginid as eu_loginid, l2.loginid as cr_loginid
          from users.loginid l1
          join users.loginid l2 on l1.binary_user_id=l2.binary_user_id
         where l2.loginid ~ '^CR'
           and substring(l1.loginid from '^\D+') in ('MF', 'MLT', 'MX')
        $$
    ) t(eu_loginid text, cr_loginid text)
)
select t.* 
  from param p
 cross join lateral dblink('cr',
         $$
           select c.loginid, c.residence, c.date_joined
             from betonmarkets.client c
             join betonmarkets.client_status s on s.client_loginid=c.loginid
            where s.status_code='ico_only'
              and (residence='gb') is $$ || p.uk_or_not_uk || $$ order by 2,1
         $$) t(loginid text, residence text, date_joined timestamp)
  left join users u on t.loginid=u.cr_loginid
 where u.eu_loginid is null
"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select 
    purchase_minute,
    market,
    sum(count_buy) as count_buy
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        count_buy
        --total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        --profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy
            --sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            --sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2
group by 1,2"}}

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
    "residence",
    sum("amount_deposit_USD") as "deposits_USD", 
    sum("count_deposit") as "count_deposits",
    count(distinct "binary_user_id") as "count_clients"
from
(
    select
    distinct
      tmp4.*,
      bc.place_of_birth,
      bc.myaffiliates_token,
      bc.residence,
      bc.citizen
    from
    (
      select
        binary_user_id,
        sum(tmp3."amount_deposit_USD") as "amount_deposit_USD",
        sum(tmp3."count_deposit") as "count_deposit",
        string_agg(distinct tmp3."currency_code", ', ') as "currencies",
        string_agg(distinct tmp3."client_loginid", ', ') as "logins"
      from
      (
        select
          tmp2.account_id,
          tmp2.source,
          tmp2.amount_deposit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta."currency_code", now()::date) as "amount_deposit_USD",
          tmp2.count_deposit,
          ta.client_loginid,
          ta.currency_code,
          ta.binary_user_id
        from
        (
          select 
            account_id,
            source,
            sum(amount) as "amount_deposit",
            count(amount) as "count_deposit"
          from
          (
            select id, account_id, amount, source 
            from transaction.transaction
            where action_type = 'deposit'
            and transaction_time >= (now() + interval '-1d')::date
            and transaction_time < now()::date
            
            except 
            
            select transaction_id, account_id, amount, source 
            from transaction.firsts
            where action_type = 'deposit'
            and transaction_time >= (now() + interval '-1d')::date
            and transaction_time < now()::date
          ) tmp
          group by 1,2
        ) tmp2 left join transaction.account ta
        on tmp2.account_id = ta.id
      ) tmp3
      group by 1
    ) tmp4 left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on bc.binary_user_id = tmp4.binary_user_id
) tmp5
group by 1
order by 2 desc, 3 desc, 1
limit 20'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 3, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select * from
    (
    select l.* from betonmarkets.client_authentication_method l right join
    (
    select client_loginid --, mx-mn, c
    from
        (
        select client_loginid, max(last_modified_date) as mx, min(last_modified_date) as mn, count(1) as c 
        from betonmarkets.client_authentication_method
        group by 1
        ) tm
    where c = 1
    --order by 3 desc
    ) r
    on r.client_loginid=l.client_loginid
    where l.status='pass'
    ) ttttt inner join 
    
    (
    select distinct client_loginid from betonmarkets.client_status
    except 
    select distinct client_loginid from betonmarkets.client_status
    where status_code='age_verification'
    ) sssss
    
    on sssss.client_loginid=ttttt.client_loginid
    order by 4 desc"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select *, loss*100/turnover as "percentage loss" from bet.daily_aggregates
WHERE CAST("bet"."daily_aggregates"."day" AS date) BETWEEN CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-30 day') AS date)
   AND CAST((NOW() + INTERVAL '-1 day') AS date)
and abs(loss)>1500
order by "day" desc, abs(loss) desc, "percentage loss" desc

'}}

SELECT
    joined,
    SUM(CASE WHEN broker_code NOT LIKE 'VR%' THEN client_cnt END) as real,
    SUM(CASE WHEN broker_code LIKE 'VR%' THEN client_cnt END) as virtual,
    SUM(client_cnt) as total
FROM new_real_virtual_account_stats(
    (SELECT start_date FROM param)::timestamp,
    (SELECT end_date FROM param)::timestamp,
    (SELECT promotion_code FROM param)::varchar,
    (SELECT deposited_only FROM param)::boolean)

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "SELECT *, pg_size_pretty(total_bytes) AS total
    , pg_size_pretty(index_bytes) AS INDEX
    , pg_size_pretty(toast_bytes) AS toast
    , pg_size_pretty(table_bytes) AS TABLE
  FROM (
  SELECT *, total_bytes-index_bytes-COALESCE(toast_bytes,0) AS table_bytes FROM (
      SELECT c.oid,nspname AS table_schema, relname AS TABLE_NAME
              , c.reltuples AS row_estimate
              , pg_total_relation_size(c.oid) AS total_bytes
              , pg_indexes_size(c.oid) AS index_bytes
              , pg_total_relation_size(reltoastrelid) AS toast_bytes
          FROM pg_class c
          LEFT JOIN pg_namespace n ON n.oid = c.relnamespace
          WHERE relkind = 'r'
  ) a
) a
order by 2,3;"}}
name: table sizes

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- temp Compliance > Self exclusion by date range
WITH params AS (SELECT
  'MX'::VARCHAR      AS broker_code,
  '2018-01-01'::DATE AS start_date,
  '2018-06-30'::DATE AS end_date,
  ''::VARCHAR AS include_countries  -- A CSV list of the only countries you want included in this report. An empty list equals all countries.
)

SELECT dbl.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$
SELECT sx.*, to_timestamp(sx.timeout_until)::date AS timeout_until_date, bc.residence
FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
JOIN betonmarkets.self_exclusion AS sx ON sx.client_loginid=bc.loginid
WHERE sx.last_modified_date >= $$|| quote_nullable(params.start_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
  AND sx.last_modified_date  < $$|| quote_nullable(params.end_date) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
AND $$||
  CASE WHEN params.include_countries > '' THEN 'bc.residence = ANY('|| quote_literal('{'|| params.include_countries ||'}') ||'::VARCHAR[])'::TEXT
       ELSE 'TRUE'
  END ||$$
AND (	-- some records have no values set, so why include those?
                sx.max_balance IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_turnover IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_open_bets IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.exclude_until IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.session_duration_limit IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_losses IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_7day_turnover IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_7day_losses IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_30day_turnover IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.max_30day_losses IS NOT NULL OR
                sx.timeout_until IS NOT NULL
                )
$$) dbl (
 client_loginid         character varying,
 max_balance            numeric          ,                                 
 max_turnover           numeric           ,                                
 max_open_bets          integer            ,                               
 exclude_until          date                ,                              
 session_duration_limit integer              ,                             
 last_modified_date     timestamp,
 max_losses             numeric   ,                                        
 max_7day_turnover      numeric    ,                                       
 max_7day_losses        numeric     ,                                      
 max_30day_turnover     numeric      ,                                     
 max_30day_losses       numeric       ,                                    
 timeout_until          numeric        ,                                   
 timeout_until_date     date            ,                                  
 residence              character varying
)

WHERE params.broker_code = ANY (ps.broker_codes)
"}}
description: temp Compliance > Self exclusion by date range

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Transaction -> Turnover & Payout by Country
-- NOTE: this report performs USD conversions at the time the report is run, based upon the totals
-- That means that the numbers can change with time as the exchange rate moves
WITH params AS (SELECT
        -- Start date
        '2018-11-01'::DATE AS start_date,
        
        -- End date
        '2018-11-30'::DATE AS end_date,

        -- Use zero, one or more of the broker codes CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX like this {} -or- {CR} -or- {CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX}
        -- Note: {} is equivalent to {CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX}
        -- Running against CR for long intervals will probably take a rather long time
        '{CR}'::VARCHAR[] AS p_broker,

        -- Use zero, one or more lower case country codes like this {} -or- {ie} -or- {ie,pt,gb}
        -- Note: {} is equivalent to requesting all countries
        '{}'::VARCHAR[] AS country
)

-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

    SELECT
        a.residence,
        a.broker_code,
        a.currency_code,
        transaction.round_amount(a.currency_code, a.turnover) AS turnover,
        transaction.round_amount('USD', a.turnover * exch.rate) AS turnover_usd,
        transaction.round_amount(a.currency_code, a.payout) AS payout,
        transaction.round_amount('USD', a.payout * exch.rate) AS payout_usd
    FROM
    (
        SELECT
            bc.residence,
            bc.broker_code,
            ta.currency_code,
            SUM(tt.amount) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type = 'buy') * -1 AS turnover,
            SUM(tt.amount) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type = 'sell') AS payout
        FROM
            transaction.transaction AS tt
        JOIN
            transaction.account AS ta ON ta.id = tt.account_id
        JOIN
            betonmarkets.client AS bc ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
        WHERE
            tt.action_type IN ('buy','sell')
            AND tt.transaction_time >= start_date
            AND tt.transaction_time < end_date) + INTERVAL '1 day'
        GROUP BY 1,2,3
        ORDER BY 1,2,3
    ) a
    LEFT JOIN data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code) exch(rate) ON TRUE
"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "

    SELECT *
    FROM
      (SELECT 
      round(sum(CASE WHEN (deals.Action = 2 AND deals.Profit>0) THEN deals.Profit ELSE 0 END), 2) as Deposit
      FROM mt5_deals_2017 AS deals
      INNER JOIN mt5_users AS users
      ON (deals.Login=users.Login)
      WHERE users.Group LIKE '%real%'
      AND DATE(deals.time) >= '2017-04-01'
      AND DATE(deals.time) <= '2017-04-30') as t
      WHERE Deposit > 0
"}}
name: The SQL query to obtain Total Deposit for real account (Whole)

    FROM
      (SELECT 
      round(sum(CASE WHEN (deals.Action = 2 AND deals.Profit>0) THEN deals.Profit ELSE 0 END), 2) as Deposit
      FROM mt5_deals_2017 AS deals
      INNER JOIN mt5_users AS users
      ON (deals.Login=users.Login)
      WHERE users.Group LIKE '%real%Champion%'
      AND DATE(deals.time) >= '2017-04-01'
      AND DATE(deals.time) <= '2017-04-30') as t
      WHERE Deposit > 0
"}}
name: The SQL query to obtain Total Deposit for the Champion group only

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "with all_rows as (
	with times as (select x as purchase_minute
				   from generate_series(now() + interval '-4h'
					  , date_trunc('minute', now())::timestamp
					  , interval  '1 min') t(x)
	), symbols as (select distinct symbol 
				   from bet.market
				   where market not in  ('stocks', 'legacy', 'cryptocurrency', 'futures', 'indices'))
	select * from symbols cross join times
	order by 2,1
)

select 
    all_rows.purchase_minute,
    all_rows.symbol,
    sum(coalesce(count_buy,0)) as count_buy
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        underlying_symbol,
        count_buy
        --total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        --profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            --bm.market, 
            fmb.underlying_symbol,
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy
            --sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            --sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2 right join all_rows
on all_rows.purchase_minute = tmp2.purchase_minute and all_rows.symbol = tmp2.underlying_symbol
group by 1,2
order by 1 desc, 3 desc"}}
name: tmp2

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT  CAST(tmp.day AS date) AS day, 
        SUM(tmp.turnover) AS sum
FROM 
    (SELECT day::date as "day", round(turnover*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code,day), 2) as turnover
    FROM bet.daily_aggregates
    LEFT JOIN transaction.account a
    ON bet.daily_aggregates.account_id=a.id
    WHERE "day" >= (now() + interval '-30 day')::date and "day" < now()::date) as tmp      
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 1 ASC'}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select 
    fmb.client_loginid||'-'||fmb.currency_code as account,
    fmb.market,
    sum((buy_price-sell_price)*exchange_rate) as company_profit,
    sum(buy_price*exchange_rate) as total_buy_usd,
    count(*) as contracts_bought
from
(
select bc1.loginid from betonmarkets.client bc1 left join betonmarkets.client bc2
on bc1.binary_user_id = bc2.binary_user_id
where bc2.loginid = {{given_loginid}}
) logins left join
(select *,data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_time) as exchange_rate 
from only bet.financial_market_bet f 
left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.id = f.account_id
left join bet.market bm
on f.underlying_symbol=bm.symbol
where purchase_time >= current_date
) fmb
on logins.loginid=fmb.client_loginid
where fmb.client_loginid <> ''
group by 1,2", 'template-tags': {'given_loginid': {'id': '799bc433-7164-bb74-df47-3f256ae2a85e', 'name': 'given_loginid', 'display-name': 'loginid', 'type': 'text', 'required': True, 'default': 'CR391325'}}}}

{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'with countries (c_value, c_name) as (
values
    ('id', 'Indonesia'),
    ('br', 'Brazil'),
    ('ng', 'Nigeria'),
    ('za', 'South africa'),
    ('th', 'Thailand'),
    ('co', 'Columbia'),
    ('ru', 'Russia'),
    ('in', 'India'),
    ('vn', 'Vietnam'),
    ('mx', 'Mexico'),
    ('gh', 'Ghana'),
    ('lk', 'Sri lanka'),
    ('zw', 'Zimbabwe'),
    ('tz', 'Tanzania'),
    ('ke', 'Kenya'),
    ('sg', 'Singapore'),
    ('pk', 'Pakistan'),
    ('ar', 'Argentina'),
    ('pe', 'Peru'),
    ('ua', 'Ukraine')
)

select 
c.c_name, sum(sss.total_buy) as "total_buy", sum(sss.company_revenue) as "company_revenue"
from
(
    select bc.residence, ttt.* from
    (
        select 
        a.client_loginid,
        tmp.account_id,
        tmp.market,
        round(tmp.total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "total_buy",
        round(tmp.company_revenue*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "company_revenue"
        from
            (
            select
                account_id,
                bm.market,
                cast(purchase_time as date) as "day", 
                sum(buy_price) as "total_buy",
                sum((buy_price - sell_price)) as "company_revenue"
            from bet.financial_market_bet fmb
            left join bet.market bm
            on bm.symbol=fmb.underlying_symbol
            where purchase_time >= now() + INTERVAL '-24 hour'
            --and market='forex'    
            and is_sold = TRUE
            group by 1,2,3
            having sum(buy_price) > 500
        ) tmp
            left join transaction.account a
            on tmp.account_id=a.id
    ) ttt left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on bc.loginid=ttt.client_loginid
) sss inner join countries c
on sss.residence = c.c_value
group by 1
order by 2 desc
limit 10
'}}
name: Top 10 country total buy and company revenue in a day

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT
    bc.residence,
    ROUND(SUM(da.turnover * exch.rate), 2) AS "turnover_USD",
    ROUND(SUM(da.loss * exch.rate), 2)     AS "revenue_USD",
    COUNT(DISTINCT ta.binary_user_id)       AS "num_clients"
FROM bet.daily_aggregates AS da
JOIN transaction.account AS ta
    ON ta.id=da.account_id
JOIN betonmarkets.client AS bc
    ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
LEFT JOIN data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, da."day") exch (rate)
    ON true
WHERE da."day" = (now() - interval '1d')::date
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 2 DESC, 3
LIMIT 20'}}
name: Top-20 countries yesterday (CR)

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select 
    purchase_minute,
    market,
    sum(total_buy) as total_buy,
    sum(profit) as profit
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2
group by 1,2"}}
name: total buy by the minute

creator: {'email': 'dwi@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Dwi', 'last_login': '2019-06-21T06:57:40.046Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': False, 'id': 53, 'last_name': 'Hadyan', 'date_joined': '2019-01-24T02:54:53.692Z', 'common_name': 'Dwi Hadyan'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 4, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT 
e."date",
round(sum(e.new_deposit_amount*e.exchangetousd_rate),2) as "new_deposits_USD"
FROM
(
  SELECT 
  data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(raw_amount.currency_code, raw_amount."date"), raw_amount.* 
  FROM
  (
    SELECT 
    cast(tf.transaction_time AS date) as "date", -- CAST to change dataType
    ta.currency_code,  
    coalesce(sum(tf.amount) filter (where tf.action_type='deposit'), 0) as new_deposit_amount -- return the first non-null in the brackets
    FROM transaction.firsts AS tf 
    LEFT JOIN 
    transaction.account AS ta
    on tf.account_id=ta.id
    
    WHERE CAST(transaction_time AS date) BETWEEN CAST((NOW() - INTERVAL '1 day') AS date)
          AND CAST(NOW()  AS date)
    
    GROUP BY 1,2 
    ORDER BY CAST(transaction_time AS date) DESC

  ) AS raw_amount
) AS e

group by 1
order by 1 asc



'}}
name: Total first depo MF

  data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(raw_amount.currency_code, raw_amount."date"), raw_amount.*

  ) AS raw_amount
) AS e

group by 1

'}}

dataset_query:
{'type': 'native', 'database': 2, 'native': {'query': 'select
    binary_user_id,
    sum(pos_usd) as pos_usd,
    sum(neg_usd) as neg_usd,
    sum(pos_count) as pos_count,
    sum(neg_count) as neg_count
from
(
    select
        account_id,
        payment_date,
        pos*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, payment_date + interval '1d') as "pos_usd",
        neg*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, payment_date + interval '1d') as "neg_usd",
        pos_count,
        neg_count,
        client_loginid,
        binary_user_id,
        currency_code,
        data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, payment_date + interval '1d') as "exchange_rate"
    from
    (
        select
            account_id,
            payment_time::date as payment_date,
            sum(amount) filter (where amount >= 0) as pos,
            count(amount) filter (where amount >= 0) as pos_count,
            sum(amount) filter (where amount < 0) as neg,
            count(amount) filter (where amount < 0) as neg_count
        from payment.payment
        where
            payment_time >= '2018-01-01' and 
            payment_gateway_code='payment_agent_transfer'
        group by 1, 2
        --order by 2 desc, 1
    ) tmp left join transaction.account ta
    on ta.id=tmp.account_id
) tmp2
group by 1'}}
name: total payment agent transfers since 2018-01-01

{'native': {'template-tags': {'threshold': {'id': 'f4fe8b2a-e780-a6cf-cb36-1e5b4cd324d5', 'name': 'threshold', 'display-name': 'Total Buy Threshold', 'type': 'number', 'required': True, 'default': '0'}}, 'query': 'select * from
(
    select
    usdder.symbol,
    --sum(usdder.total_buy) as "total_buy"
    sum(usdder.company_revenue) as "company_revenue"
    from
        (
        select 
        tmp.account_id,
        tmp.symbol,
        round(tmp.buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "total_buy",
        round(tmp.company_revenue*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code, tmp."day"), 2) as "company_revenue"
        from
            (
            select 
                account_id,
                bm.symbol,
                cast(purchase_time as date) as "day", 
                sum(buy_price) as "buy",
                sum((buy_price - sell_price)) as "company_revenue"
            from bet.financial_market_bet fmb
            left join bet.market bm
            on bm.symbol=fmb.underlying_symbol
            where purchase_time < now()::date -- + INTERVAL '-4 hour'
            and purchase_time >= (now() + interval '-1d')::date
            --and market='forex'    
            --and is_sold = TRUE
            group by 1,2,3 
        ) tmp
            left join transaction.account a
            on tmp.account_id=a.id
        --order by 3
        --limit 1000
        ) usdder
    group by symbol
) ttt
where 
--total_buy >=  500 and 
abs(company_revenue) >= {{threshold}}
and substring(symbol from 1 for 1) = 'R'
order by 2 desc'}, 'type': 'native', 'database': 2}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Rejected trades, Number of Buy Transactions at Requoted Price, Number of Buy Transaction at Requested Price
WITH params AS (SELECT
    '2017-10-01'::DATE AS start_date,   /* Inclusive, IE, "date_joined >= params.start_date" */
    '2018-01-01'::DATE AS end_date,     /* Exclusive, IE, "date_joined < params.end_date" */
    'mf'::TEXT as broker                /* <<<---- REPLACE CODE HERE */
)

SELECT t.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN dblink(LOWER(params.broker), $$
    SELECT  max(total_rejected_trades) as total_rejected_trades, 
            max(buy_tx_at_requoted_price) as buy_tx_at_requoted_price,
            max(buy_tx_at_requested_price) as buy_tx_at_requested_price
    FROM (
        select count(*) AS total_rejected_trades, 0 as buy_tx_at_requoted_price, 0 as buy_tx_at_requested_price
        from data_collection.rejected_trades
        where action_type = 'buy'
        and shortcode like '%EURUSD%'
        and trade_time >= $$ || quote_literal( params.start_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and trade_time < $$ || quote_literal( params.end_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and reason = 'SLIPPAGE'
        UNION ALL
        select 0,count (*) as buy_tx_at_requoted_price,0
        from transaction.transaction t
        inner join bet.financial_market_bet b on t.financial_market_bet_id = b.id
        inner join data_collection.quants_bet_variables d on t.id = d.transaction_id
        where b.underlying_symbol = 'frxEURUSD'
        and t.action_type = 'buy'
        and t.transaction_time >= $$ || quote_literal( params.start_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and t.transaction_time < $$ || quote_literal( params.end_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and (d.requested_price/b.payout_price)-(d.recomputed_price/b.payout_price) > 0.0175
        UNION ALL
        select 0,0,count (*) as buy_tx_at_requested_price
        from transaction.transaction t
        inner join bet.financial_market_bet b on t.financial_market_bet_id = b.id
        inner join data_collection.quants_bet_variables d on t.id = d.transaction_id
        where b.underlying_symbol = 'frxEURUSD'
        and t.action_type = 'buy'
        and t.transaction_time >= $$ || quote_literal( params.start_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and t.transaction_time < $$ || quote_literal( params.end_date ) || $$::TIMESTAMP
        and (d.requested_price/b.payout_price)-(d.recomputed_price/b.payout_price) >= -0.0175
        and (d.requested_price/b.payout_price)-(d.recomputed_price/b.payout_price) <= 0.0175
    ) as x
$$) AS t(
    total_rejected_trades       BIGINT,
    buy_tx_at_requoted_price    BIGINT,
    buy_tx_at_requested_price   BIGINT
);'}}
