WITH params AS (SELECT
        
        'MF'::VARCHAR AS broker_code, -- CH, CR, MX, MLT, MF, JP

        'EUR'::VARCHAR AS currency,      -- '' for all currencies -or- specify one 3 letter code

        '2018-02-01'::DATE AS start_date,
        '2018-02-28'::DATE AS end_date,
        
    -- Leave empty to search all payments -or- specify one or more CSV terms to narrow your search like 'BANK' or 'BANK, WIRE'
    -- the search term/s are case insensitive so 'BANK' will match "bank" or "BANK" or "Bank", etc.
        'BANK'::VARCHAR AS search_term
)
-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT
  d.transaction_time::TIMESTAMP(0)::TEXT AS transaction_time,
  d.client_loginid,
  d.credit,
  d.debit,
  d.id::TEXT AS id,
  d.remark,
  d.currency_code,
  d.staff_loginid,
  d.residence

FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN fdw.search_payment_on(ps.srvname,
    params.broker_code,
    params.currency,
    params.start_date,
    params.end_date,
    params.search_term
) AS d
WHERE params.broker_code = ANY(ps.broker_codes)
ORDER BY 1
'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- Transaction -> Turnover & Payout by Country
-- NOTE: this report performs USD conversions at the time the report is run, based upon the totals
-- That means that the numbers can change with time as the exchange rate moves
WITH params AS (SELECT
        -- Start date
        '2017-01-01'::DATE AS start_date,
        
        -- End date
        '2017-12-31'::DATE AS end_date,

        -- Use zero, one or more of the broker codes CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX like this {} -or- {CR} -or- {CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX}
        -- Note: {} is equivalent to {CR, JP, MF, MLT, MX}
        -- Running against CR for long intervals will probably take a rather long time
        '{CR}'::VARCHAR[] AS p_broker,

        -- Use zero, one or more lower case country codes like this {} -or- {ie} -or- {ie,pt,gb}
        -- Note: {} is equivalent to requesting all countries
        '{}'::VARCHAR[] AS country
)

-- DO NOT TOUCH ANY CODE BELOW HERE

SELECT t.*
FROM params
CROSS JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps
CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname,
    $$

    SELECT
        a.residence,
        a.broker_code,
        a.currency_code,
        transaction.round_amount(a.currency_code, a.turnover) AS turnover,
        transaction.round_amount('USD', a.turnover * exch.rate) AS turnover_usd,
        transaction.round_amount(a.currency_code, a.payout) AS payout,
        transaction.round_amount('USD', a.payout * exch.rate) AS payout_usd
    FROM
    (
        SELECT
            bc.residence,
            bc.broker_code,
            ta.currency_code,
            SUM(tt.amount) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type = 'buy') * -1 AS turnover,
            SUM(tt.amount) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type = 'sell') AS payout
        FROM
            transaction.transaction AS tt
        JOIN
            transaction.account AS ta ON ta.id = tt.account_id
        JOIN
            betonmarkets.client AS bc ON bc.loginid = ta.client_loginid
        WHERE
            tt.action_type IN ('buy','sell')
            AND tt.transaction_time >= $$ || quote_literal(start_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP
            AND tt.transaction_time < $$ || quote_literal(end_date) || $$::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '1 day'
            $$ || CASE WHEN array_length(country, 1) IS NOT NULL THEN 'AND bc.residence = ANY (' || quote_literal(country) || ')' ELSE '' END || $$
        GROUP BY 1,2,3
        ORDER BY 1,2,3
    ) a
    LEFT JOIN data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(a.currency_code) exch(rate) ON TRUE
      $$
    ) AS t(residence VARCHAR, broker_code VARCHAR, currency_code VARCHAR, turnover NUMERIC, turnover_usd NUMERIC, payout NUMERIC, payout_usd NUMERIC)

WHERE CASE WHEN array_length(p_broker, 1) IS NOT NULL THEN p_broker && ps.broker_codes ELSE TRUE END"}}
description: Transaction -> Turnover & Payout by Country
name: Transaction Turnover & Payout by Country

creator: {'email': 'alok@binary.com', 'first_name': 'Alok', 'last_login': '2019-10-21T06:47:00.318Z', 'is_qbnewb': False, 'is_superuser': True, 'id': 37, 'last_name': 'Tiwari', 'date_joined': '2018-11-14T06:14:10.139Z', 'common_name': 'Alok Tiwari'}
dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
  purchase_date,
  sum("volidx_buy_USD") as "volidx_buy_USD",
  sum("volidx_PnL_USD") as "volidx_PnL_USD",
  sum("forex_buy_USD") as "forex_buy_USD",
  sum("forex_PnL_USD") as "forex_PnL_USD",
  sum("indices_buy_USD") as "indices_buy_USD",
  sum("indices_PnL_USD") as "indices_PnL_USD",
  sum("commodities_buy_USD") as "commodities_buy_USD",
  sum("commodities_PnL_USD") as "commodities_PnL_USD"
from
(
select
  ta.currency_code,
  tmp."purchase_date",
  sum(tmp."volidx_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "volidx_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."volidx_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "volidx_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."forex_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "forex_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."forex_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "forex_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."indices_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "indices_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."indices_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "indices_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."commodities_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "commodities_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."commodities_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "commodities_PnL_USD"
from
(
    select
      account_id,
      purchase_time::date as "purchase_date",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='volidx') as "volidx_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='volidx') as "volidx_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='forex') as "forex_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='forex') as "forex_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='indices') as "indices_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='indices') as "indices_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='commodities') as "commodities_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='commodities') as "commodities_PnL"
      
    
    from bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
    on fmb.underlying_symbol=bm.symbol
    where purchase_time >= (now() + interval '-7d')::date
    and purchase_time < now()::date
    group by 1,2
) tmp left join transaction.account ta
on ta.id=tmp.account_id
group by 1,2

) tmp2
group by 1
order by 1 desc'}}

    sum(tmp3."num_clients")::bigint as "num_clients"

    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            ta.binary_user_id,
            sum(tmp.turnover) as "turnover",
            sum(tmp.loss) as "loss",
            count(distinct ta.id) as "num_clients"

        (
            select * from bet.daily_aggregates

        ) tmp left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id=tmp.account_id
        group by 1,2
    ) tmp2 left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on bc.binary_user_id=tmp2.binary_user_id
) tmp3
group by 1
order by 2 desc, 3
limit 20'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': ' with  temp1 as (
   select purchase_date,
      residence,
      --sum(buy) as "buy",
      sum(buy*exchange_rate) turnover 
   from 
   (
    select 
      c.residence,
      purchase_time::date as "purchase_date",
       data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(acc.currency_code, purchase_time) exchange_rate,
      sum(buy_price)  as "buy"
    from bet.financial_market_bet fmb 
    inner join transaction.account acc
      on acc.id = fmb.account_id
    inner join betonmarkets.client c
      on c.loginid = acc.client_loginid
    where purchase_time >= (current_date + interval '-7d')::date
      and purchase_time < current_date
    group by c.residence,
      purchase_time::date,
      data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(acc.currency_code, purchase_time) 
      order by buy desc)t
     group by purchase_date,
          residence
       )
 
 select *
    --sum(turnover)
    --sum(buy) 
 from temp1 tm 
 where tm.residence in 
             (select t.residence
             from temp1 t
             group by t.residence
             order by sum(t.turnover) desc
             limit 6)
 order by residence, purchase_date
    --   */'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "WITH params AS (
    SELECT 
        '2016-08-27'::TIMESTAMP AS frm,                  -- search for clients that joined after this point in time
        true AS include_virtual,                       -- true: include virtual accounts, false: only real-money accounts
        false AS exclude_clients_without_utm_source     -- true: only look for clients having a defined utm_source, false: take all clients into account
)


-- please don't change anything below this line
, cl AS (
    SELECT s.srvname, c.loginid, c.date_joined, c.first_payment
      FROM pg_catalog.pg_foreign_data_wrapper w
      JOIN pg_catalog.pg_foreign_server s ON (s.srvfdw=w.oid)
      JOIN params ON TRUE
      JOIN dblink(s.srvname, $$
               SELECT DISTINCT ON (c.loginid)
                      c.loginid, c.date_joined, p.payment_time
                 FROM betonmarkets.client c
                 JOIN transaction.account a ON a.client_loginid=c.loginid
                 LEFT JOIN payment.payment p on p.account_id=a.id
                WHERE c.date_joined>='$$ || params.frm || $$'
                ORDER BY c.loginid, p.payment_time
           $$) c(loginid TEXT, date_joined TIMESTAMP, first_payment TIMESTAMP) ON TRUE
     WHERE w.fdwname IN ('postgres_fdw', 'dblink_fdw')
       AND (params.include_virtual OR s.srvname<>'vr')
       AND EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM dblink(s.srvname, $$
               SELECT 1 FROM pg_class c JOIN pg_namespace n ON n.oid=c.relnamespace
                WHERE c.relname='client' AND n.nspname='betonmarkets'
           $$) t(i int))
)
, u AS (
    SELECT *
      FROM dblink('users', $$
               SELECT u.email, l.loginid, u.utm_source, u.utm_medium, u.utm_campaign, u.app_id
                 FROM users.binary_user u
                 JOIN users.loginid l ON l.binary_user_id=u.id
                WHERE NOT $$ || (SELECT exclude_clients_without_utm_source FROM params) || $$ OR u.utm_source IS NOT NULL
           $$) t(email text, loginid text, utm_source text, utm_medium text, utm_campaign text, app_id bigint)
)
SELECT u.email, u.loginid, u.utm_source, u.utm_medium, u.utm_campaign, u.app_id, cl.date_joined, cl.first_payment
  FROM u
  JOIN cl ON u.loginid=cl.loginid
;
"}}

-- this report will only display the credit transfers done by payments team 
-- after a MT5 account is disabled and the client's balance is to be credited to their CR account

-- MODIFY THE CODE ACCORDINGLY

WITH params as (
  SELECT
    'CR'::VARCHAR AS broker_code,
    '2019-01-01'::DATE AS start_date, -- YYYY-MM-DD
    '2019-01-31'::DATE as end_date -- YYYY-MM-DD
)

-- DO NOT TOUCH CODE BELOW

SELECT

db.*

FROM params
JOIN betonmarkets.production_servers_v2() AS ps ON UPPER(params.broker_code) = ANY(ps.broker_codes)
CROSS JOIN dblink (ps.srvname, $$
  select acc.client_loginid, acc.currency_code, pa.amount, pa.staff_loginid, pa.remark, pa.payment_time::DATE
  from payment.payment pa
  join transaction.account as acc ON pa.account_id = acc.id

  and pa.payment_time::date <= $$|| quote_literal( params.end_date ) ||$$
  ORDER by payment_time desc
$$) db (

client_loginid VARCHAR,
currency_code VARCHAR,
amount NUMERIC,
staff_loginid VARCHAR,
remark VARCHAR,
payment_time DATE

)
"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
  purchase_date,
  sum("volidx_buy_USD") as "volidx_buy_USD",
  sum("volidx_PnL_USD") as "volidx_PnL_USD"
  --sum("forex_buy_USD") as "forex_buy_USD",
  --sum("forex_PnL_USD") as "forex_PnL_USD",
  --sum("indices_buy_USD") as "indices_buy_USD",
  --sum("indices_PnL_USD") as "indices_PnL_USD",
  --sum("commodities_buy_USD") as "commodities_buy_USD",
  --sum("commodities_PnL_USD") as "commodities_PnL_USD"
from
(
select
  ta.currency_code,
  tmp."purchase_date",
  sum(tmp."volidx_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "volidx_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."volidx_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "volidx_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."forex_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "forex_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."forex_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "forex_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."indices_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "indices_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."indices_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "indices_PnL_USD",
  sum(tmp."commodities_buy") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "commodities_buy_USD",
  sum(tmp."commodities_PnL") * data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tmp."purchase_date"::timestamp) as "commodities_PnL_USD"
from
(
    select
      account_id,
      purchase_time::date as "purchase_date",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='volidx') as "volidx_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='volidx') as "volidx_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='forex') as "forex_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='forex') as "forex_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='indices') as "indices_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='indices') as "indices_PnL",
      sum(buy_price) filter (where bm.market='commodities') as "commodities_buy",
      sum(buy_price - sell_price) filter (where bm.market='commodities') as "commodities_PnL"
      
    
    from bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
    on fmb.underlying_symbol=bm.symbol
    where purchase_time >= (now() + interval '-7d')::date
    and purchase_time < now()::date
    group by 1,2
) tmp left join transaction.account ta
on ta.id=tmp.account_id
group by 1,2

) tmp2
group by 1
order by 1 desc'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "-- VR - real - deposits - turnover - analysis v1
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2017-01-01'::DATE AS vr_start_date,  -- The earliest VR join date
                                        -- these dates are inclusive
  '2018-02-01'::DATE AS real_start_date,-- The earliest real money join date -and- the start of monetary aggregations
  '2018-02-28'::DATE AS real_end_date   -- The latest VR & real money join date -and- the end of monetary aggregations
)
,vr AS (
    SELECT d.*
    FROM dblink('vr', $$
        SELECT
            binary_user_id,
            MIN(date_joined) AS date_joined,
            residence
        FROM betonmarkets.client
        WHERE date_joined >= $$|| quote_literal((SELECT vr_start_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
          AND date_joined  < $$|| quote_literal((SELECT real_end_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1d'::INTERVAL
        GROUP BY 1,3
    $$) d (
        buid BIGINT,
        date_joined TIMESTAMP,
        residence VARCHAR
    )
)
,notvr AS (
    SELECT d.* FROM betonmarkets.production_servers() AS ps CROSS JOIN dblink(ps.srvname, $$
        SELECT
            bc.binary_user_id AS buid,
            bc.residence,
            min(bc.date_joined) AS date_joined,
            abs(transaction.round_amount('USD', SUM(tt.amount * exch.rate) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type='deposit'))) AS deposits_usd,
            abs(transaction.round_amount('USD', SUM(tt.amount * exch.rate) FILTER (WHERE tt.action_type='buy'))) AS turnover_usd
        FROM betonmarkets.client AS bc
        LEFT JOIN transaction.account AS ta
          ON ta.client_loginid=bc.loginid
        LEFT JOIN transaction.transaction AS tt
          ON tt.account_id=ta.id
                  -- these txn filters help PG use the indexes, otherwise we end up with a full scan of the txn table, a killer on CR
          AND tt.transaction_time >= $$|| quote_literal((SELECT real_start_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
          AND tt.transaction_time  < $$|| quote_literal((SELECT real_end_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1d'::INTERVAL
        LEFT JOIN data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta.currency_code, tt.transaction_time) AS exch(rate) ON TRUE
        
        WHERE bc.date_joined >= $$|| quote_literal((SELECT real_start_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
          AND bc.date_joined  < $$|| quote_literal((SELECT real_end_date FROM params)) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1d'::INTERVAL

        GROUP BY 1,2
    $$) d (
        buid BIGINT,
        residence VARCHAR,
        date_joined TIMESTAMP,
        deposits_usd NUMERIC,
        turnover_usd NUMERIC
    )
)

SELECT
    COALESCE(vr.residence, notvr.residence) AS country_code,
    bcc.country_name,
    COUNT(vr.*) AS vr_opened,
    COUNT(notvr.*) AS real_opened,
    SUM(notvr.deposits_usd) AS deposits_usd,
    SUM(notvr.turnover_usd) AS turnover_usd,
    AVG(notvr.date_joined - vr.date_joined) AS avg_conversion_interval,
    'VR: '|| params.vr_start_date ||' Real: '|| params.real_start_date ||' - '|| params.real_end_date
FROM vr
-- This join assumes we only want real clients who are siblings to VR in this run. There are real clients who have signed up without first doing VR. These are not included in this report
LEFT JOIN notvr
     ON vr.buid=notvr.buid
    AND vr.date_joined <= notvr.date_joined   -- only real clients who joined after the VR client
LEFT JOIN brands_binary_countries AS bcc
    ON bcc.country_code = COALESCE(vr.residence, notvr.residence)
CROSS JOIN params
GROUP BY 1,2,8
ORDER BY 2"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 11, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'SELECT 
CASE WHEN length(custom_limits) > 2 then 'Watch and Limit' ELSE 'Watch only' END as watching_type,

 a.*

FROM 
(SELECT
x.loginid,
v.vals->>'reason' AS reason,
v.vals->>'updated_by' AS updated_by,
v.vals->>'updated_on' AS updated_on,
v.vals->>'custom_limits' AS custom_limits
FROM 
    (SELECT value FROM chronicle WHERE category='app_settings' AND name='quants.custom_client_profiles' ORDER BY "timestamp" DESC LIMIT 1) AS c
CROSS JOIN json_object_keys((c.value::json->>'data')::json) AS x(loginid)
CROSS JOIN LATERAL (
SELECT (((c.value::json->>'data')::json)->>x.loginid)::json AS vals
) AS v
) as a'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': "select 
    ((date_part('hour', purchase_minute)*60 + round((date_part('minute', purchase_minute)/5)::numeric,0)*5))/60 as gmt_time_five_minute_period,
    market,
    sum(count_winning)/sum(count_buy) as fraction_winning
    --sum(count_winning) as count_winning
from
(
    select 
        currency_code,
        purchase_minute,
        market,
        count_buy,
        count_winning
        --total_buy*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as total_buy,
        --profit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(currency_code, purchase_minute) as profit
    from
    (
        select
            ta.currency_code,
            bm.market, 
            date_trunc('minute', purchase_time) as purchase_minute, 
            count(*) as count_buy,
            count(*) filter (where sell_price > 0) as count_winning
            --sum(buy_price) as total_buy,
            --sum(buy_price - sell_price) as profit
        from only bet.financial_market_bet fmb left join bet.market bm
        on bm.symbol = fmb.underlying_symbol
        left join transaction.account ta
        on ta.id= fmb.account_id
        where purchase_time >= current_date
        and purchase_time < date_trunc('minute', now())
        group by 1,2,3
    ) tmp
) tmp2
--where market not in ('volidx', 'r100Group')
group by 1,2
order by 1"}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'select
    "residence",
    sum("amount_deposit_USD") as "deposits_USD", 
    sum("count_deposit")::bigint as "count_deposits",
    count(distinct "binary_user_id")::bigint as "count_clients"
from
(
    select
      tmp3_in_USD.*,
      bc.residence,
      bc.binary_user_id
      from
      (
        select
          tmp2_agg_acc.amount_deposit*data_collection.exchangetousd_rate(ta."currency_code", now()::date) as "amount_deposit_USD",
          tmp2_agg_acc.count_deposit,
          ta.client_loginid
        from
        (
          select 
            account_id,
            sum(amount) as "amount_deposit",
            count(amount) as "count_deposit"
          from
          (
            select id, account_id, amount, source 
            from transaction.transaction
            where action_type = 'deposit'
            and transaction_time >= (now() + interval '-1d')::date
            and transaction_time < now()::date
            
            except 
            
            select transaction_id, account_id, amount, source 
            from transaction.firsts
            where action_type = 'deposit'
            and transaction_time >= (now() + interval '-1d')::date
            and transaction_time < now()::date
          ) tmp_except 
          group by 1
        ) tmp2_agg_acc left join transaction.account ta
        on tmp2_agg_acc.account_id = ta.id
      ) tmp3_in_USD left join betonmarkets.client bc
    on bc.loginid = tmp3_in_USD.client_loginid
) tmp5
group by 1
order by 2 desc, 3 desc, 1
limit 20'}}

dataset_query:
{'database': 2, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': '-- Yng Shan analysis
WITH params AS (SELECT
  '2017-11-15'::DATE AS report_day
)

SELECT t.* FROM params, dblink('dc',
            $$
                SELECT DISTINCT ON (op.financial_market_bet_id)
                        op.financial_market_bet_id,
                        op.marked_to_market_value
                   FROM accounting.end_of_day_open_positions AS op
                   JOIN accounting.end_of_day_balances       AS eod
                     ON eod.id = op.end_of_day_balance_id
           -- As of 11/24/17, in practice it looks like the values in here always fall on a day boundary 00:00:00
           -- i.e. 2017-11-24 00:00:00 reflects the pricing at the open of the day and so the close of the previous day (we'll call the reporting day)
           --
           -- However, since the field is a timestamp instead of a simple date, we cannot make the assumption that this will hold true in the future,
           -- nor can we safely assume that some anomaly will not introduce multiple entries for a given "date" since there is no constraint to prevent this.
                WHERE eod.effective_date >= $$|| quote_literal( params.report_day ) ||$$::TIMESTAMP
                  AND eod.effective_date < $$|| quote_literal( params.report_day ) ||$$::TIMESTAMP + '1 day'::INTERVAL
-- for MF only, we can look for a pattern on the fmb.id.. they end in the digit zero
AND right(substring(op.financial_market_bet_id::text from '\d+'),1) = '0'
                ORDER BY op.financial_market_bet_id, eod.effective_date
        
            $$
            ) AS t(fmb_id TEXT, mtm NUMERIC)'}}
description: Yng Shan analysis
name: Yng Shan analysis

dataset_query:
{'database': 9, 'type': 'native', 'native': {'query': 'Select  deals."Symbol",
       Count(Distinct(users."Login"))   AS Total_Clients,
             Count(Distinct(users."Login")) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)  AS Agent_Linked_Clients,
              

       SUM("Volume"/10000) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Volume,
       SUM(("Profit")*-1)  FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Profit,
       SUM(("Storage")*-1) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0) AS Total_Storage,
       CASE WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 10 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 25 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 50 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 75 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(2.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'Volatility 100 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.75/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 10 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.25/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 50 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       WHEN "Symbol" = 'HF Volatility 100 Index' THEN SUM((ROUND((("Volume"/10000)*(0.10/-2)),2))) FILTER (Where users."Agent" != 0)
       ELSE '0' END AS Agent_Commissions
   FROM mt5_deals_2019 AS deals
   JOIN mt5_users AS users ON users."Login" = deals."Login"
    
 
  and date_part('year',deals."Time")='2019'
   and "Symbol" IN ('Volatility 10 Index', 'Volatility 25 Index','Volatility 50 Index','Volatility 75 Index', 'Volatility 100 Index','HF Volatility 10 Index','HF Volatility 50 Index','HF Volatility 100 Index')
   and "Entry" IN (0,1,3)
   and "Action" IN (0,1)
 
   and users."Group" LIKE '%costarica%'
group by deals."Symbol"'}}

Count(Distinct(mt5_users."Login")) FILTER (Where mt5_users."Country" = 'Indonesia') As Indonesia
